title: rhubarb punch
directions: Simmer rhubarb in the 5 cups of water, then strain it into a glass bowl.
Add sugar and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.
Before serving, add soda.
Serve over ice.

title: great fish
directions: Make a doubled tinfoil dish with a tinfoil top.
Put fillet in and cover with 1/2 of the sauce (combined ingredients).
Cover with tinfoil top and either put on grill or bake for 10 minutes or until fish flakes to touch.
Baste with sauce halfway through.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes in 11 x 7-inch greased pan.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine with 2 cups of cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of pan.

title: potato puffs(leftover mashed potatoes)
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Add mashed potatoes, salt, milk, flour and baking powder.
Make mixture stiff so it drops off spoon into a deep fryer set at 375°.
If not crowded in fryer, they should turn themselves; if not, turn.
Cook until golden brown (check inside one to make sure it's cooked).
Serve hot.
Delicious if you sprinkle them with powdered sugar.
We like to dip them in ketchup as we eat them.

title: almond sugar
directions: Place sugar in a small bowl.
Sprinkle with vanilla and almond extracts.
With a fork, stir to blend well.
Store in an airtight container.
Use to sweeten coffee or tea to taste.
Makes 1 cup.

title: southern fried corn
directions: Cut corn from ears of corn; scrape cob.
Combine corn, flour and water.
Cook in skillet with hot oil.
Stir.
Cook 2 minutes. Add seasonings and butter.
Continue cooking until corn is tender.

title: pumpkin walnut cake
directions: On wax paper, sift together first 5 ingredients.
In large bowl, beat eggs on high speed until yolks and whites are combined. Gradually add sugar, beating until lemon color (thick).
Beating continually, pour in corn oil.
With mixer at low speed, blend in sifted dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into ungreased angel food pan. Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: easy cherry crisp
directions: Pour pie filling into an 8-inch square pan.
In small bowl, combine flour and oleo (use fingers to cut in oleo).
Add oats, brown sugar and spices and mix well.
Sprinkle mix over cherries and bake at 350° for 35 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serve plain or with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: company potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; slice potatoes almost through at 1/4-inch intervals.
Put in baking dish greased with butter.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, onion powder and garlic powder over sliced potatoes. Bake until done (about 30 minutes).
Sprinkle cheese on top and return to oven to melt.
Serve hot.
Sprinkle parsley over the potatoes.

title: no-bake crunch balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and oil; blend well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dates, nuts and vanilla.
Blend well and pour into greased shallow cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars or squares after cooling.

title: taco salad
directions: Tear up lettuce; add other ingredients.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until lemon color.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Combine together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture, small amount at a time, alternating with milk.
Make flour the last ingredient.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: simple toasted pecans
directions: Toss pecans with mayonnaise to moisten lightly.
Arrange in jelly roll pan.
Dot sparingly with butter.
Stirring occasionally, bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle, if desired, with salt.
Cool thoroughly before storing.

title: spicy pumpkin cookie
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until light.
Add eggs and pumpkin and blend well.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Add raisins, nuts and dry ingredients that have been sifted together; mix well.
Chill dough; drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Will make 4 dozen cookies.

title: pear butter
directions: Quarter and core pears; place in large pan.
Add enough water to prevent sticking.
Cook until soft.
Press through sieve of food mill.
Measure pulp.
Combine 2 quarts pulp with remaining ingredients.
Cook 15 minutes or until thick, stirring.
Put in hot jar.
Process in hot water bath 180° for 10 minutes.
Cool. Test for seal.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook rice about half done.
Take a knife and cut down toward center of cabbage and around core of cabbage.
Put into large pot, about 1/2 or 3/4 full of water.
Bring to a simmer.
Start taking leaves off and put on side to cool.
Saute onions until they start to get tender.

title: country grits and sausage casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to boil.
Stir in grits then reduce heat and cook 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine grits and cheese in a large mixing bowl and stir until cheese is melted.
In separate bowl combine eggs, milk, thyme and garlic salt.
Mix well. Add to egg mixture a small amount of hot grits mixture, stirring well.
Stir in remaining grits.
Add cooked sausage.
Pour into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, remove from refrigerator and let stand 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
This recipe may be halved.

title: paula's chicken divan
directions: Lay broccoli on bottom of casserole dish, then chopped chicken. Mix remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs; put on top of chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix milk into room temperature cream cheese very slowly (to prevent curdling); then add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill one hour; serve with corn chips, celery or any other raw veggies preferred.

title: swiss plum kuchen
directions: For crust,
mix
butter, flour, 1 teaspoon of the sugar and 1 beaten
egg.
Mix
like pie dough.	Line 8 x 12-inch pan with this dough.
Mix
cups
sugar, sour cream, 2 well beaten eggs and cinnamon and pour over crust into which halved fresh or frozen plums
have
been placed (cut side up in even rows).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked bacon and chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Wrap bacon strips around chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: tortilla soup(serves 8. preparation :20.  cook :30.  total :50.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a soup pot, heat 1/2 cup beef stock; add onions and garlic and simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, corn, tomatoes and remaining 4 1/2 cups broth; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer soup 20 to 25 minutes.
Add cilantro, hot sauce and chili powder to soup.
Adjust seasonings if desired. Cut each corn tortilla into 8 strips.
Spray lightly with nonstick vegetable spray and bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden. Remove and cool.
Serve 1 cup hot soup in bowl and garnish each serving with 3 tortilla strips and 2 tablespoons grated Cheddar cheese.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Heat blackberries, tapioca and sugar until real hot.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top; dot with butter.
Mix Bisquick, egg and sugar until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of blackberry layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: frozen citrus pie
directions: Beat lemonade.
Add softened ice cream and fold in Cool Whip. Pour
into crust and freeze at least 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8 and can be refrozen.

title: oven-fried fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Melt the butter in a 9 x 13 pan in the oven.
While it melts, combine everything else except the fish, in a pie plate.
Dip the fish around in the melted butter, dip each piece of fish in the crumb mixture and return it to the baking pan.
Bake the fillets for 20 to 25 minutes, or until the fish flakes with a fork.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place
into a salad bowl. Garnish with carrot curls and sprigs of parsley.

title: bischoff bean bake bonanza
directions: Fry bacon and onion just until onion is tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in brown sugar, vinegar, mustard, garlic salt and salt; simmer, covered, 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients into the shape of a ball.
Chill 2 hours, roll in chopped pecans.

title: hearty ham and waffle sandwich
directions: In small saucepan, combine 1/2 cup honey and apple juice. Stir over medium heat until heated through. Set aside and keep warm.

title: chicken artichoke casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring
until
thickened and smooth.
Add red pepper, garlic and
cheese; stirring until smooth.
Blend in chicken, mushrooms and artichoke hearts.
Pour into 2 quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika. Serves 6 persons or 3 Moffos.

title: babom's jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
In greased Bundt pan, put one layer of mix.
Then sprinkle on cinnamon liberally.
Then cover with the remaining mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blue plum cake
directions: In mixing bowl beat eggs, add sugar and salad oil.
Set aside. Sift
flour,
soda
and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture. Fold
in plums and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for
one hour in 350° oven.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when taken from pan.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, sugar, spice, flour and soda together. Pour onto cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot venison stew
directions: Marinate
cubed venison in French dressing for 12 to 24 hours. Drain
off
dressing
and	place venison in crock-pot. Stir
in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Boil carrots for 15 minutes.
Add ground beef, potatoes, chili powder, salt, tomato soup and tomatoes.
Cook for about 45 minutes. Add beans and peas.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Serve with French bread.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine and boil first 5 ingredients 1/2 minute.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and oats.
Stir and drop on wax paper.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Crumble thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 6 ingredients and put on top of potatoes.
Put corn flakes on top and drizzle melted butter over corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no fail kraut
directions: Put chopped cabbage in clean sterilized jars.
Combine all other ingredients and let dissolve.
Then pour slowly into jars over cabbage and seal lids.
It's ready to eat in 4 weeks and doesn't turn dark.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cream butter and sugar in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition; blend in vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Blend in melted chocolate.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cut horizontally into 3 even layers.
Spread filling between layers.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in mixture.
Stir pecans, dates and cherries in.
Chill overnight.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover sides and bottom.
Mix the last 3 ingredients. Pour over mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: avocado and tomato salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a non-reactive bowl.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together strawberries, eggs and oil.
Sift dry ingredients into strawberry mixture.
Stir to blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts. Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or 4 small loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out dry.

title: fat-free hollandaise sauce
directions: In electric blender, combine Egg Beaters, lemon juice and red pepper; blend at medium speed just until mixed.
Without turning off blender, pour in liquid Butter Buds in a slow, steady stream. Continue blending until mixture is smooth and thick.
Keep warm in double boiler until ready to serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread refried beans in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning; spread over beans.
Sprinkle cheese, tomatoes and onions on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: baby shrimp with rice
directions: Boil rice with water to cook rice.
In a hot skillet or wok, put in oil and fry the eggs.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook over low heat until sugars dissolve. Cook to soft ball stage (238° on candy thermometer).
Cool to lukewarm.
Heat until of spreading consistency.
Use on your favorite cake recipe.

title: pork tenderloin rosemary
directions: Trim meat and rub with mixture of dry mustard, salt and pepper. Brown in butter in heavy skillet, then transfer to baking dish. Heat currant jelly in skillet to loosen drippings and add 3 tablespoons butter.
Simmer until jelly melts.
Add about 1 teaspoon rosemary and mix.
Pour over tenderloins and cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, turning once.
Mix 2 tablespoons flour with 1 cup half and half and pour over meat.
Cover again and bake 45 to 60 minutes more.
Serve:
Slice in 1/2-inch slices.
Gravy should still be warm; if not, heat and serve with meat.

title: donna's taco dip
directions: Mix together and put in bottom of dish the cream cheese and 1 package taco seasoning.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix with 1 package taco seasoning mix and water.
Pour hamburger mix over cream cheese mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: tropical fruit cooler
directions: Add hot or boiling water to gelatin in a large mixing bowl; stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and fruit juices; stir in sugar.
Chill.
Just before serving, mash or whip bananas until smooth and creamy.
Beat into mixture.
Add ginger ale.
Garnish with fluted slices of banana, pineapple, strawberry, lime, lemon or orange (use any one or any combination).

title: banana salad
directions: Cook together sugar, flour, egg and Milnot.
Add vanilla.
Let cool.
In a bowl, make a layer of 1/2 bananas, 1/2 pudding mixture and 1/2 peanuts.
Repeat layer, using remaining ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spring breeze cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add fruit.
Spoon into crust. Chill in the refrigerator at least 3 to 4 hours.

title: souper easy quiche
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and cream.
Mix well.
Sprinkle cheese, meat and vegetables evenly over pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake in 350° oven until center is set (about 50 minutes).
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: susie's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Remove and chop stems.
Drain caps.
Saute onion, pepper, sausage, garlic and stems until tender.
Add bread crumbs, cheese, herbs, salt and pepper.
Mix together.
Add chicken broth as needed to make stuffing moist.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps.
Place in baking dish, stuffing side up.
Add remaining chicken broth and enough water to make 1/4-inch of liquid in bottom.
Bake at 325°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jose's secreto salsa(jose's secret sauce)
directions: Put all the ingredients in the blender and push grind for about 5 seconds.
Easy to make and tastes great with any Mexican dish or tostado chips.
!Que Maravilla!
(How Marvelous!)

title: green bean casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart baking dish with butter.
Cover sides and bottom of buttered dish with 1/2 of the cracker crumbs.
Place in layers the beans, cheese and onion (make 2 layers).
Cover with soup.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Drizzle 3 or 4 tablespoons melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut chicken
wings
into 2 pieces, discarding the tips. In a small bowl, combine butter and garlic powder.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Dip chicken into butter mixture, then
into	crumb
mixture.
Place	on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°, or until done.

title: butterscotch sponge pie
directions: Whip egg whites until stiff.
Mix other ingredients listed. Add egg whites.
Bake 45 - 50 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: walnut squares
directions: Combine and cream first 3 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Melt chocolate in microwave.
Cool and add to sugar and butter mixture.
Add vanilla and salt.
Add one egg and beat 5 minutes.
Add second egg and beat 5 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill 4 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cheese crab dip
directions: Mix the two cheeses together until soft.
Add the rest of the ingredients in order given.
Serve as a warm dip.

title: ham salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on bread.

title: egg patties
directions: Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cook sausage in skillet, breaking up as it cooks.
Drain fat and blot with paper towels.
Sprinkle crumbled, cooked sausage over bread slices. Sprinkle cheese over top.

title: apple cake
directions: Let sugar and apples stand until syrup forms, then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in bananas. Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add to banana mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes, or until tests done. (The riper the bananas the longer the baking time, up to an hour.)

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place rice in Pyrex dish.
Mix chicken soup and water.
Heat. Then pour over rice.
Place chicken breast on rice.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, oil, water and eggs. Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
(To save time, instead of making cookies, bake in an ungreased 8 1/2 x 11-inch dish.)
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes for cookies or 30 minutes for 8 1/2 x 11-inch dish.

title: poor college student tuna melts
directions: Check the roll for mold; it doesn't matter if they're stale. Slice in half and place open-faced on cookie sheet.
Put oven on broil.
Open tuna and place in bowl.
Mix with dressing and pickles.
Spread on rolls.
Cut any visible mold off of cheese and lay slices on tuna mixture.
Broil until cheese is fully melted. Eat off of paper plate or napkin.
Very good with water and saltine crackers.
If you're lucky enough to get a care package, a cookie is an excellent dessert.

title: no fat zucchini muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, mix flour, oats, sugars, soda, salt and baking powder until blended.
In another bowl, beat egg, Butter Buds and 1/2 cup warm water and vanilla.
Mix all together.
Add zucchini and lemon peel.
Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Bake 20 minutes or until brown.
Cool. Roll in cinnamon sugar.
Makes 11 or 12 regular size muffins.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crush all but 3 or 4 Oreos in a flat dish, then mix 8 ounces Cool Whip, sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over Oreos.
Mix chocolate pudding.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle remaining chopped Oreos on top and refrigerate.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add salsa, yogurt and chili powder.
Put half of meat mixture in 2-quart casserole, then put a layer of chips and a layer of cheese on top of this.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Spread grated cabbage in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle canning salt over cabbage and let stand 1 hour.
Boil the vinegar, sugar, water, celery seed and mustard seed for 1 minute.
Cool.
Chop carrot and mango.
Squeeze the juice out of cabbage and put into another pan.
Mix well all ingredients.
Put into Ziploc bags, seal and freeze.
Will keep 1 year.
Preparation time is 2 hours. Yields 15 or more servings.
Very good!

title: sticky buns
directions: Mix yeast and water.
Add sugar, salt, egg and flour.
Knead into soft dough.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Grease large cake pan. Spread with brown sugar, nuts and syrup.
Roll dough out in oblong shape 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with oil and 1/3 cup white sugar. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up.
Slice in 1-inch pieces.
Place cut side down in pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb with water and sugar until tender.
While hot, add jello.
Mix until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Drain apricots, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup liquid.
Heat to boiling.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved. Cool.
Chop apricots and combine with remaining ingredients. Stir into gelatin.
Place in 2-quart mold and refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: lipton berry fiz
directions: In a large pitcher, combine instant tea powder, water, lemonade and raspberries; chill.
Just before serving, add lemon soda.
Serve with ice.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: preservative base for perfect sandwiches
directions: Blend thoroughly.
This will keep indefinitely, but unless you are making in quantity, halve the recipe.
(Use as substitute for mayonnaise.)

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Add 2 teaspoons spaghetti sauce mix.
Add Ragu or picante sauce.
Add grated cheese and heat slowly until melted.
Add chicken that has been cut into small pieces.
Stir and serve hot.

title: maple-bacon oven pancake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease and flour rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Beat baking mix, sugar, eggs, milk, syrup and 1/2 cup of the cheese with hand beater until smooth; pour into dish.
Bake uncovered until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle pancake with remaining cheese and the bacon.
Bake uncovered until cheese is melted, 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Serve with maple-flavored syrup if desired. Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all soups and water with butter.
Spread rice in casserole dish.
Pour 1/2 of soup mixture over rice.
Lay chicken breasts on mixture.
Dripple rest of soup on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: mimi's ice cream cake
directions: Line a large pan or deep pan with aluminum foil.
Slice the cake into small pieces.
Line the pan with pieces of cake.
Cover with soft ice cream.
Add another layer of cake pieces.
Add another layer of ice cream.
Continue to do this until pan is full.
Pack cake and ice cream tight.
Cover pan with aluminum foil.
Put in freezer until ready to serve.
Remove from freezer, take off aluminum foil, turn cake upside down.
Cover with whipped topping, slice and serve.

title: joni's spaghetti sauce
directions: In a skillet, brown hamburger and drain.
Add salsa, paste, sugar and salt to taste. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve with cooked spaghetti.

title: curried goat
directions: Cut goat flesh into pieces.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic; add scallions, onions and curry powder.
Let stand for at least 1/2 hour.
Scrape off seasonings and lightly brown in hot oil.
Add about 1 pint of hot water and all seasonings, except onions.
Cook over medium heat until tender, about 40 minutes.
Add the second tablespoon of curry powder, potatoes, butter and the onions about 10 minutes before removing from the fire.
The gravy should be of a consistency not to need any thickening.
Serve hot with plain boiled rice with chutney, nuts, raisins and grated coconut.

title: 59 diner pancakes
directions: Combine liquid ingredients and dry ingredients separately. Mix until smooth.
Let batter rest for 10 minutes. Cook on a preheated, lightly greased griddle for 1 minute.
If desired, sprinkle fresh blueberries, pecans, bananas or strawberries on uncooked side.
Turn pancakes and finish cooking.
Makes about 10 pancakes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, chocolate and salt in a saucepan. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir at least half of hot mixture into egg yolks. Then blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour immediately into baked pie shell.
Finish with pie meringue.

title: saucy franks
directions: Score hot dogs in corkscrew fashion; lightly brown in butter. Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes. Add green pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve in rolls.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saute salt pork in Dutch oven. Remove and reserve.
Add onion and saute until golden. Add potatoes, clam broth, salt and pepper. Simmer until potatoes are tender, but not mushy.
Add clams and simmer for 5 minutes. Add milk and butter.
Heat, but do not allow to boil. Add cooked salt pork.
Adjust seasoning and serve with saltines.

title: jezebel sauce 2
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well. Serve over cream cheese with crackers as an appetizer or on baked ham.
Sauce will keep in refrigerator for months.
Vary amounts of various ingredients for hotter or milder sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put all together and mix with rotary beater.
Put in uncooked pie shell.
Cook slowly at 300° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: southwestern linguine with shrimp
directions: Bring 2 1/2 quarts of unsalted water to a boil in a 4 1/2-quart Dutch oven or soup pot.
When the water boils, add the noodles and cook until just tender, 10 to 11 minutes.

title: coke salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and Jell-O well.
Heat Cokes to boiling; pour over cream cheese and Jell-O mixture.
Let stand 2 hours before putting in refrigerator.
Add pineapple and pecans when slightly firm.

title: avocado-cottage cheese salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: cream cheese carrot muffins(yummy for breakfast)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease or line 12 muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine quick bread mix, water, oil, pineapple and egg.
Stir to moisten all ingredients.
Fill prepared muffin cups 3/4 full. Place 1 mounded teaspoonful of soft cream cheese on top of batter in each muffin cup.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: barbecue(serves 1)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Place in baking dish and bake until moisture evaporates.

title: swordfish and wild mushrooms
directions: Soak
mushrooms
in
1 quart warm water for 30 minutes. Squeeze
out
excess
water
and remove stems.
Chop mushrooms into quarters;
save water.
Brush baking dish with olive oil. Lay steaks
in
layer.
Salt
and
pepper
to
taste.
Heat 1 tablespoon
olive
oil
in
heavy bottomed skillet over medium heat;
add garlic.
Saute, stirring until garlic turns golden. Add mushrooms;
saute for 2 minutes.
Add wine and stir until almost evaporated.
Add the soaking liquid from the mushrooms. Add thyme, rosemary and more salt and pepper, if needed.
Turn up
heat
and cook until most of the liquid has evaporated and the
mushrooms are glazed.
Stir in 3 tablespoons parsley and remove
from
heat. Douse
the
fish
with 1 tablespoon lemon juice
and
pour
on the mushrooms so the fish steaks are covered.
Top with the remaining lemon juice.
Cover and place in refrigerator for at least 1 hour, preferably 5 or 6 hours.

title: black walnut or pecan pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and shortening.
Add milk and flour alternately, mixing well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add flavoring and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Place in a cold oven. Set heat to 325° and bake 1 hour.
Increase heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: flaky pastry crust
directions: Set oven heat to 400°. Combine flour and salt in mixing bowl. Cut in shortening and butter until lumps are pea-size. Add water 1 spoon at a time and stir until
mixture is moistened. Press into a ball and chill 45 minutes.

title: venison casserole
directions: To cook, brown in heavy pan in fat from 1/4 pound of salt pork, salad oil and butter or margarine after dredging meat in flour and paprika.
Brown on high heat.
Remove from fat; add thinly sliced onions.
Stir onions until lightly browned.
Add consomme and red wine; bring to boil.
Add meat; cover and simmer over low heat 1 to 2 hours, or until meat is tender.

title: evelyn's spinach casserole
directions: Squeeze water from spinach.
Line bottom of casserole with spinach, then layer eggs, sour cream and soup.
Sprinkle crumbs and chives on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
May add tuna or ham layer after eggs.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first five ingredients in order given.
Add layer of diced ham and cheese.
Add sugar and vinegar to mayonnaise and mix thoroughly.
Spread over cheese and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except the nuts) in a bowl using a fork.
Roll into a flat ball.
Place in a small plate; sprinkle with the nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: beef sauce
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan. Add the onions and the garlic. Cook until tender, or about 5 minutes. Add the beef and fry until browned.
Add the other ingredients. Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 3 1/2 pints.
Keep on a low flame.

title: apple crunch
directions: Spread sliced apples in buttered baking dish (9 x 9). Cover the apples with white sugar and sprinkle with cinnamon. Mix flour and brown sugar and cut in oleo until it resembles corn meal. Cover apples with this mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: buttery bacon shrimp
directions: In saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add chives, garlic powder and pepper.
Stir well.
Dip shrimp into butter and roll in cracker crumbs, coat well.
Layer shrimp in baking dish.
Add remaining crumbs to baking dish and pour butter over the top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch container place frozen hash brown potatoes mixed with chopped green onions.
Place grated Cheddar cheese on top of mixture.
Mix with sour cream and cream of chicken soup. Cover with bread crumbs.
Melt margarine and pour over ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: hero sandwich a la "bill kirkland"
directions: With sharp knife, cut bread lengthwise in half.
Cut bread crosswise to make 2 portions.
On the bottom half of the sliced bread, arrange the tomato and egg.
Add salami, cheese, ham, cucumber and onion.
Sprinkle with pepper salad oil and parsley. Sprinkle lightly with crushed red pepper.
Sprinkle generously with olive oil.
Sprinkle lightly with vinegar.
Place top of bread over sandwich filling.
Think fondly of "Bill" and enjoy.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix together cream cheese and egg.
Add sugar 1 cup at a time. Mix well.
Add chocolate that has cooled.
Add vanilla and milk. Beat to desired consistency.
May chill a few minutes if desired.

title: spinach rosito
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook on low. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add rice; stir another 3 minutes.
In a separate pan bring broth to a boil.
Slowly add 1 cup broth to 1 cup rice, then add spinach and thyme.
Add rest of broth.
Stir and add salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
The rice should be cooking a total of 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple nut cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, salad oil and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift all dry ingredients together and add to mixture. Blend together good.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Pour into a 10 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Sift flour and add soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening with sugar, eggs and vanilla flavoring.	Add flour mixture alternating with 1 cup buttermilk.	Mix thoroughly.
Pour into large greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fruity dessert
directions: Boil water. Add Jell-O and cranberry sauce until dissolved. Let stand. Add pineapple, celery, apple and walnuts. Refrigerate.

title: pasta with olives and basil
directions: Remove seeds of tomatoes; dice.
Cube black olives, garlic and basil leaves.
Combine everything.
Marinate for 1 to 2 hours.

title: chicken breasts and rice
directions: Brown chicken breasts in butter in heavy skillet.
Place in deep baking dish, skin side up.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, covered. Remove cover and bake an additional 25 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Make pastry.
Roll half thin and use it to line 12-inch deep baking pan or dish.
Roll other half thin and cut into strips.
Put berries, 1 cup sugar and water into a saucepan.
Cook until berries are soft.
Mix flour and 1/4 cup sugar and add to berries.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened.
Pour into pan. Dot with butter.
Cover with remainder of pastry strips.
Bake at 425° in preheated oven until pastry is brown.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat 5 minutes at medium speed.
Pour in tube pan.
Cook in preheated oven for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except brown sugar and catsup; mix well. Turn into loaf pan. Make indentions across loaf. Combine sugar and catsup and drizzle on loaf. Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: Sauce:
Cook meat, onion and garlic until meat is brown. Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, paste, water, basil, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook and cut beets. Boil brine until sugar is dissolved.
Put into jar and process recommended time.

title: zuni bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Beat eggs, shortening and honey thoroughly and add to flour mixture with milk.
Stir until smooth. Fold in whole seeds.
Grease bread pan and flour bottom and spoon in batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes in pan.
Remove, but do not slice until cold.

title: stuffed cabbage hungarian style
directions: Core to free leaves of large head of cabbage.
Fill cavity with salt.
Cover with boiling water and parboil 5 minutes or until soft.
Drain and trim thick center vein of each leaf. Combine ground pork, rice, parsley, egg, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Place heaping spoonful on each cabbage leaf and roll up; tuck in sides.
Alternate layers of cabbage rolls and sauerkraut in a large kettle.
Cover with soup and water.
Add bay leaf and cloves.
Cover and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Add more water as needed.
Ideal for all day crock-pot cooking, also.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
except gelatin, mix gelatin with 1/2 cup water, boil 1/3 cup water and add to gelatin mixture. Combine all
other ingredients with gelatin and put in casserole
that has
been
oiled
with
vegetable
oil.
Chill for several hours.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well and add the flour.
Let rise until double.
No kneading is necessary.
When double, split in half.
Roll each half and spread with the margarine, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Roll up and cut.
Let rise until double in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with icing while warm.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Make crust from crescent rolls.
Fit on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Mix together other ingredients and spread on crust.
Add any combination of vegetables desired. Chill and serve.

title: skillet herb roasted chicken
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour, sage and thyme.
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.

title: busy day goulash
directions: Boil macaroni according to package directions. Drain in colander and set aside. In same pan, combine oil, onion, pepper and beef. Saute until beef is brown and onion and pepper are soft. Add oregano and salt. Add soup and mix well. Add cooked macaroni and mix again. Stir and heat until heated through. Add parsley and grated cheese to taste.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Mix last four together and pour over first 6.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat the sugar and Crisco for 10 minutes.
Add the next 3 ingredients and mix well.
Alternately add the flour and mix well after each addition.
Add the eggs, 1 at a time, and mix well after each addition.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix vegetables, cheese and bacon.
Combine salad dressing, sugar and vinegar in another bowl.
Pour over vegetable mixture and mix well.
Serve immediately.

title: brickle cookie candy
directions: Spray
an 11 x 17-inch pan with Pam.
Lay saltines in a layer on
bottom
of
pan.
Melt
butter
and
sugar.
Boil 3 minutes. Pour
mixture
over crackers.
Cook in 400° oven for 10
minutes. Watch
them carefully.
They may burn.
Take pan out of
oven
and lay chocolate bars on top to melt.
Sprinkle nuts over
all and cool in refrigerator a few hours.
Take out and cut with pizza cutter or break into pieces like brittle.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup until soft ball forms when dropped into cold water.
Add peanut butter and beat until thick.
Pour on large platter.
Cut when still warm.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add nuts.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Use powdered sugar to dip hands into as you roll the balls.
Melt the chocolate and paraffin over low heat.
Dip balls into this mixture one piece at a time, holding each with a toothpick.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: rio ramen
directions: Brown ground chuck; mix taco seasoning with ground chuck as instructed on package and simmer.
Cook Ramen noodles as instructed on package, except mix seasoning packet in noodles with ground meat that is simmering.
Drain noodles and rinse with hot water.
On dinner plate, spread 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of noodles; top with Cheddar cheese to cover top of noodles.
Top with ground chuck mixture.
Top with the following:
taco sauce (5 tablespoons), shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes and crushed nacho chips.
"Mix together and enjoy."
One package of Ramen noodles makes 2 servings.

title: crockpot chicken and rice
directions: Slice mushrooms.
Remove skin from chicken.
Spray 12 inch skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Brown mushrooms, onion, and chicken pieces on all sides over medium heat approximately 15 minutes.
Stir in seasonings and transfer to crockpot.
(Can be refrigerated overnight.)
Start crockpot on low.
When ingredients are heated, add rice.
Cook until done.
Per serving:
265 calories, 25g. protein, 27g. carbohydrates, 6g. fat, 67mg. cholesterol, 20% calories from fat.

title: christmas bread
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, egg and bananas together.
Add flour and soda.
Add to other mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips, cherries and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine flour and salt; coat meat.
Brown in hot shortening. Add soup, 2 1/2 cups water, onion and basil.
Cover and bake about 1 hour in a 370° oven.
Add potatoes, carrots and wine; bake 1 hour longer.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook to boiling, zucchini and onion, 5 minutes; drain. Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in zucchini and onion. Combine stuffing and butter; spread 1/2 on bottom of pan.
Add zucchini mixture, then remainder of stuffing on top.
Add butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup with a little water

title: spiced cranberry sauce
directions: Peel orange skin,peel well. Put peel, cider, cinnamon,cloves and sugar into saucepan. Simmer 10 min.Remove spices. Add prewashed cranberries to saucepan, simmer 10 min or until cranberries POP!
Chill.

title: sliced refrigerator pickles
directions: Pour brine over sliced onion and cucumbers.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator.
Stir everyday for 5 days.
At this time you can pack in jars and return to refrigerator or leave in original container.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together and spread in 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Put cottage cheese through a sieve to make smooth.
Mix sugar and flour; add to cottage cheese.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla, salt and cream.
Mix. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake another 10 to 15 minutes or until light golden and cooked through. Pie may fall when taken out of oven.
Do not overbake, it sets easily.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Wrap each breast in slice of beef, then bacon strip.
Place on a lightly greased oven dish.
Mix soup and sour cream and cover chicken with mixture.
Dust with paprika.
Bake 3 hours at 275°. Mixture will curdle if baked at too high temperature.

title: easy jello salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello and stir to dissolve.
Add pineapple with juice.
Set bowl in refrigerator until it begins to firm.
Remove and add Cool Whip with a wooden spoon or wire whisk. Spread in 13 x 9-inch oblong pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar (can put butter and cream cheese in microwave for 30 seconds to soften).
Mix together the milk, pudding and Cool Whip; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Layer crumbled Oreo cookies and pudding mixture, ending with cookies.
Refrigerate.

title: oreos and ice cream
directions: Layer in order given in a rectangle or round Tupperware container with lid.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add broccoli; stir until thawed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in greased casserole. Heat thoroughly in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 12 servings.

title: homemade chicken soup(with a little help from campbell's)
directions: Boil chicken breasts for approximately 15 minutes.
Remove chicken from pan and boil rice in broth.
When rice is done, add cans of soup, celery, pepper and parsley.
Pick chicken apart and toss in pan.
Use milk to thin out if necessary.
Stir a lot while cooking.
Serve with a loaf of bread.
You can make this in 30 minutes and there'll be enough to serve at least 2 people.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Wrap chicken breasts in foil and bake at 400° until tender, about 1 hour.
Cool and bone, saving drippings.
Cut chicken into strips.
Grease 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place half the tortilla strips on bottom of the pan, then half the chicken, then half the cheese.
Mix chili sauce, soups, drippings and milk.
Pour half of this mixture on top of cheese.
Repeat steps, ending with soup mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: soy sauce dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Serve with fresh raw vegetables.

title: shrimp cracker spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread on crackers, party bread, etc.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy; beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended. Blend in melted butter, chocolate morsels and walnuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pudding cake
directions: Tear cake into little pieces and cover bottom of 5 dessert dishes.
Mix pudding according to directions on box; pour over cake.
Spread fresh strawberries over pudding mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate if not served immediately.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Use on beef, pork or chicken.

title: green tomato catsup
directions: Mix first five ingredients and put 1/3 cup salt in enough water to cover.
Let it sit overnight and drain.
Add sugar, vinegar, 1 cup water and pickling spices; boil on stove for 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Cook in hot water for 10 minutes.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in pie shell.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rosy punch
directions: Mix together over ice ring.
Serves 30.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place in a greased loaf pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes; let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked onions
directions: In a 9x13 buttered casserole alternate layers of onions, potato chips and cheddar cheese.
Pour mushroom soup and milk over the top of the onion mixture.
Sprinkle cayenne pepper on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and a pinch of salt. Place in buttered 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and egg until crumbly and pour over the apples.
Drizzle the melted butter over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon zucchini bread
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Sift together remaining five ingredients (except nuts).
Add dry ingredients to zucchini batter.
Mix. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Add nuts to the batter.
Divide batter evenly into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Cool 10 minutes on rack.
Turn out of pans.
Cool completely and refrigerate.
Freezes well.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, vegetable shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the 5 beaten eggs and mix well.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mix alternately with milk.
Mix well and add flavorings.
Pour in a 10-inch tube pan and bake in middle of slow oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Dampen the minced onions with water and set aside.
Combine the cream cheese, sour cream, picante sauce and chopped green chiles.
Drain excess water off the minced onions and add to the mixture; stir well.
Spread generously over tortillas.
Roll up tightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, slice crosswise, making pinwheel pieces.
Will keep for several days in refrigerator.

title: mrs. clark's lemon dessert
directions: Separate eggs; beat together egg whites and 3/4 cup of sugar until stiff.
Combine egg yolks with lemon rind, lemon juice, sugar and whipped cream.
Fold yolk mixture into beaten egg whites.
Line a spring-form pan with cookies of your choice (sugar cookies work well).
Pour egg mixture into pan and freeze for at least 8 hours.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, green peppers and onion in greased baking dish (3-quart).
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Mix mushroom soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: apple crisp(pears also)
directions: Place the apples and water in baking dish.
In another bowl, combine flour, sugar and cinnamon; cut in butter.
Spread this mixture over the apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna-lettuce bundles
directions: Trim stalks from lettuce leaves.
In a small bowl, toss together tuna, cabbage, zucchini and sprouts.
Stir in dressing; season to taste with pepper.
Spoon 1/2 of the salad mixture in center of each leaf.
Roll up leaves, enclosing filling.
Secure lettuce bundles by slipping a bell pepper ring over each.
Place bundles seam side down on plate.
Makes 1 serving.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Calorie Count:
190 calories per serving.

title: crock pot macaroni & cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in lightly greased crock pot.
Cut slices of cheese and put on top.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low heat.

title: latkes(potato pancakes)
directions: Shred or grate potatoes.
Combine onion, eggs, salt and pepper in large mixing bowl.
Pat dry potatoes with paper towels; add to onion mixture and mix thoroughly.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Drop potato mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into oil. Cook until crisp and golden on both sides.
Serve with applesauce and/or sour cream.

title: salsa fresca
directions: Blend all ingredients except Tabasco sauce.
Add the Tabasco sauce to taste.
Serve with tortilla chips as an appetizer or as an accompaniment to any Mexican food.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl with electric mixer, cream butter, sugar and egg until fluffy.
Mix in molasses, corn syrup and milk.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves, mixing until well blended.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and shape into 1 1/2 inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until tops are puffed.
Do not overbake or the cookies will not be soft.
Cool 1 to 2 minutes on baking sheets, then remove to racks to cool.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and peppers together and sprinkle with salt; let stand overnight.
Drain.
Add hot pepper, vinegar, spices (tied in cheesecloth bag) and sugar.
Allow to boil slowly until tender and cooked down some.
Pack boiling hot into sterilized jars.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix together lightly; form into small balls (1 1/2 inches). Heat small amount of fat and brown.
I use Crisco.
Add about 1/2 cup of water.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Thicken the pan drippings slightly and serve hot with meat balls.

title: hot sausage and cheese puffs
directions: Remove
sausage
from
casings.
Cook in large skillet, breaking up
with
fork, until no longer pink.
Drain off fat. Spoon
into
large
bowl.
Cool
completely.
Add
remaining ingredients.
Mix until just blended.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Place on large cookie sheets 2-inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until puffed and browned.
Makes 120.

title: red hot salad
directions: Cook red hots and water until dissolved.
Pour over Jell-O. Stir to dissolve.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat until fluffy.
Add topping.
Fold into gelatin.
Combine apple and lemon juice.
Fold into gelatin along with marshmallows and nuts.
Chill.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter.
Remove from heat and add sugar, cornmeal, vinegar, vanilla and eggs.
Bake in uncooked pie shell at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Melt margarine or butter. Add onion and saute until it is slightly browned and curled on ends.
Add salt and pepper.
Place mushrooms on top of the onion and stir in. Saute until mushrooms are cooked, but firm, about 10 minutes.
Add 3 tablespoons lemon juice to mixture and cook for 30 seconds. Serve hot. May be made up ahead and reheated in microwave oven.
Very tasty over steaks, hamburgers or plain as a side dish.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Put all dry ingredients together.
cut in shortening. Combine juice and eggs.
Fold in berries and nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees until golden on top.

title: mini rolls
directions: Melt butter.
Mix herbs and Parmesan with melted butter.
Pour half in an 8-inch pan. Place mini rolls in pan, making sure all are touching.
Pour remaining mixture over top of biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned cushaw pie
directions: Cook cushaw in water until tender.
Drain.
Add the butter, sugar and cream, beating with mixer after each addition.
Add eggs and salt.
Pour into crusts.
Grate nutmeg on top.
(You have to use whole nutmeg, freshly grated, to get the right flavor.
A basic cream pie with a cup of cushaw added is also delicious.) Bake old fashioned pie at 350° until filling sets.

title: pecan pasties
directions: Soften oleo, cheese, add flour and mix until smooth.
Make into 36 small balls.
Flatten and press into very small muffin tins. Combine brown sugar, oleo, vanilla, and egg.
Mix and add nuts. Fill shells and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Double this for 36 muffins.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Add enough water to syrup to make 1 cup liquid.
Bring to a boil and dissolve gelatin in hot liquid.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Chill until thick, but not set. Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple, celery and nuts.
Pour into 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on a bed of lettuce.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese, milk and mayonnaise.
Top with pecans and chill.

title: wassail
directions: Mix, heat and serve.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend and cool.
Add beaten eggs.
Sprinkle yeast in warm water; dissolve and add flour to it.
Mix well.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 4 hours.
About 3 hours before using, roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Pat melted butter on top and fold like a pocketbook.
Place in greased pan and allow to rise until double. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ham and spaghetti casserole
directions: Combine ham broth and both cheeses.
Heat until melted; add milk.
Bring to a boil.
Thicken with flour thickening.
Combine spaghetti, ham, peas and cheese sauce.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour or until heated through.

title: sugar-free pineapple cream pie
directions: Lightly mix together pineapple and dry pudding mix.
Add sour cream and mix well. Pour into cooked pie crust and refrigerate for 3 hours. Top with Cool Whip and return to refrigerator for 1 more hour to set.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut off tips.
Wash wings and pat dry.
Put in roasting pan. Mix all ingredients together; pour over wings.
Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for 3/4 hour.
Remove foil; turn wings.
Baste every 15 minutes until wings are soft and done.

title: refrigerated bran muffins
directions: Mix bran, salt, water and buttermilk together; let cool. Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir into bran mixture.
Combine flour and soda; add to bran mixture, stirring until moistened.
Will keep in refrigerator in covered container for 4 to 6 weeks.
Spoon out what you need into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 375° until done, approximately 25 minutes.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Layer crushed wafers.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs; layer on wafers.
Layer pineapple (strained), heavy cream and second layer wafers.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: striped jello
directions: Layer 1:
5 ounces orange Jell-O, 5 ounces hot water, 5 ounces evaporated milk.

title: pumpkin bran muffins
directions: Combine bran cereal, pumpkin, milk, corn syrup and egg whites in one bowl; set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and baking powder together and add to first bowl, stirring just until moistened; add raisins.
Spoon batter into 12 section muffin tin coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes; cool out of pans on wire rack.
Makes 12.
Based on 12 servings.
Per serving: 159 calories; 43g fat; 284mg sodium; .25mg cholesterol.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine oil, onion, green pepper and ground beef.
Brown the mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Add milk and eggs.
Add the self-rising corn meal to the liquid and mix until smooth.
Add shortening and mix until smooth. Add peppers, cheese and corn; mix smoothly.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: orange spiced yams and apples
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In greased 12 x 7-inch baking dish, arrange apples and raisins.
Set aside.

title: jack-o-lantern cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup pan.
Prepare and bake 1 cake mix according to package directions.
Cool completely. Repeat with remaining cake mix.
In a medium bowl, combine both containers of frosting.
Remove and reserve 1/4 cup of the frosting.
Add red and yellow food coloring to remaining frosting; blend well to make orange frosting.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, chestnuts, sauteed onions, mayonnaise and grated cheese.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle about 1 cup dressing mix on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into pieces (1 x 1 1/2-inch); set aside.
Combine next 5 ingredients; dip chicken into batter.
Fry in hot oil until done (golden).

title: baked lemon pudding
directions: Sift 1 cup sugar with flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg yolks until light, add lemon juice, rind, butter and milk and beat well.
Stir in flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding remaining sugar (1/2 cup), one tablespoon at a time, then fold into mixture. Pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Set in a pan containing hot water, 1/2 inch deep, and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Chill.
If desired, spread with whipped cream.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend mayonnaise and sour cream.
Mix remaining ingredients. Chill overnight.
Serve with bite size pieces of Hawaiian bread. Good on chips or crackers too!

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix vinegar and soda in small cup and let sit.
Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and small amount of red coloring.
Add to the creamed mixture, then add rest of coloring.
Add buttermilk, salt and flour alternately.
Add vanilla, vinegar and soda. Stir well, then pour into two 8 or 9-inch layers (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and split layers lengthwise making 4 thin layers.

title: cranberry nut loaf
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Put egg, sugar, orange juice and oil in blender.
Blend only until mixed. Add cranberries and nuts; blend.
Add dry ingredients and stir until barely moistened.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until a tester inserted comes out clean.
Cool before slicing.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine the kraut, onion, celery, peppers and pimentos. Combine the sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over kraut mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: hearty chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread across bottom and sides to form shell.
In large bowl, combine chicken, vegetables, soup, milk and seasonings; pour into shell.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, until onions are golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mom's coconut pie
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding by package directions.
Add sugar substitute, coconut, vanilla and coconut flavorings.
Melt the margarine and add to graham cracker crumbs.
Pat this into pie tin for the crust.
Refrigerate and serve with Cool Whip for topping.

title: cheesy chicken and broccoli macaroni
directions: Spray large skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Add chicken. Cook and stir 2 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.

Stir in broth. Bring to a boil. Stir in macaroni. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover.	Simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Add Velveeta cheese and broccoli. Stir until cheese spread is melted.	Makes 6 servings.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add milk, potatoes and Crisco.
Add eggs; mix.
Add sugar, salt and 4 cups flour, using 1 cup flour to knead dough.
Place in greased bowl; cover and refrigerate.
Shape into rolls; let rise.
Bake for 15 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: In saucepan combine jello with boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Fold in strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Turn half of mixture into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread with sour cream. Soon on rest of mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: sole and lobster in the florentine style
directions: Wash
the
fillets
in	cool
water and place them in a bowl. Add the lemon juice and toss the fillets in the bowl to coat them with the lemon juice.
Let them stand for 30 minutes at room temperature or
longer
under refrigeration.
Butter a baking pan large enough to
hold
fillets
folded
in half. Arrange the fillets so that
they do not overlap; fold fillets in 3 if necessary.	Pour
the
white
wine	over
the
fillets first, then salt and pepper
them to taste.
Butter a piece of wax paper large enough to cover the baking pan or use tinfoil. Bake fillets in preheated
oven for 15 minutes, or until cooked.
Do not overcook.

title: katsu-don(pork on rice-a japanese main dish)
directions: Cut roast
or
pork
loin into slices.
Salt and pepper each slice.
Flour
each
slice,
then dip in beaten egg, then bread crumbs.
Deep
fry
in
oil.
Remove
and cut into small pieces. Saute
onion.
Put
meat and onion in a deep pan with Aji Mirin, soy sauce, sugar and beaten egg.
Boil until thick. Serve over rice.

title: fire and ice dip
directions: Mix first four ingredients and pour over blocks of cream cheese.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix the ingredients and freeze.
About two hours prior to use, take out of freezer and thaw.
Add 1/2 gallon of strawberry ice cream and a bottle of chilled ginger ale.
You may add another bottle, if needed.

title: shredded lettuce salad
directions: Shred vegetables in crock.
Pour 1 cup sugar over all!

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Add both cans of corn and sour cream. Stir in cornbread mix until well blended. Pour into greased pan and bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all together and simmer.
Serve over preferred pasta.

title: easy chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Put ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool slightly; stir and spread on cake.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together
the first four ingredients and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt the chocolate chips and spread on the top.
Let cool and cut into small squares.

title: beef-mushroom quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Prick sides of pie shell with fork. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove pie shell from oven and reduce heat to 350°.
Brown hamburg and drain.
In bowl, mix cream of mushroom soup, milk, eggs, spices and red pepper sauce.
Add mushroom pieces, hamburg and cheese.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serve with tossed green salad of your choice.

title: italian zucchini boats
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut off stem end of each zucchini. Lengthwise slice off top third of each zucchini; hollow out, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
In medium saucepan, bring water, oleo and 1/2 teaspoon salt to rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk, egg and potato flakes until well combined.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon 1/8 of potato mixture (about 1/2 cup) into each zucchini shell.
Place each stuffed shell on piece of foil; wrap loosely.
Repeat with remaining potato mixture and shells. Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Open foil packets; continue baking 15 to 20 minutes longer or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 8.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water; let stand for 5 minutes. Drain.
Combine flour and cinnamon.
Beat sugar, shortening and eggs until fluffy.
Add flour mixture and milk; beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in carrots, raisins and nuts.
Spread into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan or 2 (9-inch) round cake pans for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Frost with lemon cream cheese frosting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In frying pan with 1 tablespoon oil saute onion, pepper and celery
until
tender.
Add
broccoli,
soups and cheese. Bring to boil
and
add rice.
Pour in baking dish and bake 15 minutes at 400° or until heated through.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Put cut-up chicken in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix
soup
and broth; pour over chicken.
Add desired
vegetables.	Beat
together butter or margarine, flour and milk.	Spoon
batter
over the layers. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: green peas and asparagus casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish layer peas, asparagus spears, chopped mushrooms, eggs and cheese.
Pour mushroom soup over all and top with final layer of cheese and Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until cheese is brown and bubbly.

title: chocolate chip banana muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add bananas, Crisco, water and eggs.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spoon into muffin pan and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shrimp provencal style(yield:  6 servings)
directions: Heat 1/2 cup of olive oil in a large saute pan.
Saute the shrimp in small batches; keep undercooked.
Remove with a slotted spoon to a strainer or colander.
Add the remaining oil to the skillet and reheat.
Saute the onions, garlic and fennel for about 1 minute.
Add the chili pepper.
Deglaze the pan with the wine and reduce by half.
Add the tomato strips and sun-dried tomatoes and cook for a few minutes.
Add the parsley, oregano, salt and pepper and combine with the cooked shrimp.
Sprinkle the scallions over the shrimp and garnish with few sprigs of basil.
Serve immediately.

title: chinese coffee cake
directions: Beat sugar and flour; add to beaten eggs.
Add baking powder. Quickly add 3/4 cup scalded milk.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Melt one stick oleo and pour over cake which has been punched with holes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cinnamon.

title: homemade hamburger helper
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer raw potato slices. Set aside.
In a bowl, combine both cans of soup; do not add water.
Pour soup mixture over potatoes.
Layer ground beef over soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veggie spread
directions: Mince upper branches and leaves of celery.
Grate large lower portions, removing strings.
Combine celery, carrots, onion, salt, garlic powder and 1 tablespoon parsley flakes.
Mix thoroughly with cream cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining tablespoon parsley flakes.
Refrigerate overnight for flavors to blend.
Serve with crisp breadsticks or spread on crackers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let cheese reach room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Form into small	balls.	Bake
in ungreased pan at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Place pineapple, oranges and cherries in a large bowl. Mix juices from oranges and pineapple (approximately 3 1/2 cups) with pudding and tapioca. Bring to a boil, stirring to prevent scorching. Pour over fruit and gently stir thoroughly.
Chill. Fold in bananas just before serving.

title: hamburger pot roast
directions: Line 9 x 12-inch baking pan with tinfoil.
Make hamburger patties and place in pan.
Top with sliced onion, potatoes and carrots.
Add sliced cabbage if desired.
Salt and pepper and seal in tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain.
Combine all other ingredients and place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After top browns, cover with lid until done.

title: octoberfest ribs
directions: In a Dutch oven, layer all ingredients in order. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 2 to 3 hours until tender. Serves 6.

title: meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Beat egg whites until fluffy, about 2 minutes.
Continue beating and slowly add sugar.
Beat in vinegar and vanilla.
Cover cookie sheet with foil, shiny side up.
Drop mixture by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour; turn heat to 100° and bake another 20 minutes.
Check that they don't brown. They're ready when they can be gently peeled off foil.
Just before serving, put dollop of whipped cream in each center and top with berry.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix together and press into an oblong baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes or light tan in color.
Do not overbake.
Chill.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream with zucchini.
Add carrots and season with salt and pepper.
Add 2 tablespoons margarine.
Mix stuffing with melted margarine.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs.
Combine rest of crumbs in casserole.
Place reserved crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, cinnamon and baking powder together.
Set aside.
Cream the margarine, shortening and sugar together.
Mix flour mixture with creamed mixture, adding milk with vanilla. Beat egg whites and fold in mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured tube pan.
Let stand in pan 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Whip bananas until light.
Cream butter and sugar and add eggs. Sift flour and soda.
Add to butter and eggs.
Combine this mixture with the finely chopped pecans, then add crushed bananas.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
1 loaf. (This banana bread is quite moist and not very sweet.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until frothy; add sugar gradually.
Add flour, then syrup, flavoring and butter.
Cook slowly at 350°.

title: romano yogurt salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor or blender.

title: the best bloody mary ever
directions: Put ice in glass. Pour in gin. Add Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce, pepper juice and juice from squeezed lime. Stir. Add Clamato juice. Chop celery fine and stir into drink. Sprinkle celery salt and ground pepper on top of drink. Enjoy!

title: chocolate lovers cake
directions: Melt 1 cup margarine.
Stir
in
cup cocoa and add water. Bring to a
boil.	Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, mix flour, brown
sugar,
baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add cocoa mixture and beat
well.
Stir
in
cup
Eagle Brand milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour
into
greased
jellyroll
pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, or until cake springs back when touched.	Don't overbake.
In
a
small
pan,
melt
cup margarine, the remaining
cup cocoa and Eagle Brand milk. Stir in powdered sugar and nuts.
Spread on warm cake.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as usual; chill until lightly jelled.
Add drained pineapple, marshmallows.
Let set until firm.
Spread sauce over gelatin.
Whip cream and add cream cheese.
Spread whip cream over sauce.

title: deep fried cinnamon puffs
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, yeast, sugar, salt and cinnamon. Mix well. In saucepan, heat milk, water and butter until warm (120-130 degrees). Butter does not need to melt. Add to flour mixture, add eggs and beat at low speed until moistened. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed. Cover, let rise in warm oven (turn oven on lowest setting for one minute, turn off) for 20 minutes.

title: sugar-free fudge brownies
directions: In a bowl add flour, baking powder, salt and walnuts.
In a saucepan, melt together the butter, unsweetened chocolate, raisins, dates and apple juice.
Add to dry ingredients and mix in eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in an 8-inch square pan.

title: strawberry wet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.
Cool.
Punch holes in cake.
Pour icing over cake.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, milk, flour, baking powder and flavoring.
Divide batter in half.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Parboil ribs and soy sauce until ribs are tender.
Drain.
Add honey to the tomato sauce and baste.
Let stand about 1 hour. Place in rotisserie basket and barbecue about 30 minutes until nicely browned. Baste often with the sauce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes.
Add seasonings, chicken, soup, sour cream and spaghetti.
Mix thoroughly.
Place into a shallow, buttered, 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ginger ball cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Mix in egg and molasses.
Sift and measure flour.
Sift again with the soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt.
Stir the dry ingredients into the mixture in the bowl.
Mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll each one in granulated sugar.
Place at least 4 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: brownies plus
directions: Add 1 to 2 teaspoons hot water to Marshmallow Creme.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Mix dry cake mix and margarine.
Reserve 1 1/4 cups for topping.
Put rest of mix in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Press evenly.

title: sugar cakes
directions: Cream together the sugars and then the butter and lard.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Add the hot water last.
Drop by teaspoon on greased or sprayed pan and bake at 350°.

title: butterscotch cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, melt morsels and butter. Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press 1/2 of mixture in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl beat cream cheese, vanilla and egg.
Mix well and pour into pan.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool at room temperature; chill before cutting.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sunday chicken breasts and rice
directions: Put uncooked rice in shallow baking dish.
Mix both soups and mushrooms together.
Spoon this mixture over dry rice, then spoon the wine over this.
Place the chicken in next.
Over the chicken, sprinkle dry onion soup.
Seal tightly with heavy-duty foil and bake 2 hours in a 350° oven. Do not open while baking.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute zucchini, onions, peppers and

garlic in oil until tender. Stir in the tomatoes, tomato sauce, beans, jalapeno and seasonings. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Yield: 16 servings.

title: ranch style hash
directions: Brown ground beef in margarine; add tomatoes, peppers, onion and rice.
Season with basil, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with slices of Velveeta cheese.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together	gently.
Pour
into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Serve warm or cold.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender. Drain off fat.
Combine meat and onion with noodles, cheese, soup, 1 cup water, green and red pepper, chili sauce, salt and a dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Turn into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine crumbs and butter. Sprinkle on top and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: corn chowder
directions: Add onion to pressure cooker and brown.
Add potatoes, ham, water, salt and pepper.
Close pressure cooker and cook 5 minutes. Let pressure drop.
Add corn, milk and butter.
Reheat.
Thicken chowder, if desired.

title: cherry fruit cake
directions: Grease pan (tube or two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans).
Add flour, baking powder and salt into bowl and mix.
Add fruit and mix, then beat eggs and rum together and pour over fruit.
Mix well and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Brush with glaze.

title: violet's prunella nut cake
directions: Mix sugar, Wesson oil, eggs, prunes, nuts and buttermilk. Sift remaining ingredients together and add to the mixture.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in angel food tube pan at 350°.
This cake freezes good.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Dissolve soda in water.
Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs to creamed mixture.
Add spices, cocoa and salt to flour. Gradually add flour and soda water mixture to creamed mixture; beat well.
Add apples and pecans.
Stir in vanilla; mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Remove from oven.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: lemon ice
directions: Boil sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Strain juice and add to syrup.
Add grated rind.
Chill and freeze.
Stir several times during the freezing process.

title: toasted sandwiches
directions: Grind together first 4 ingredients.
Add catsup and mayonnaise.
Spread on buns.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Sandwiches may be frozen.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Sift powdered sugar.
Mix peanut butter and graham cracker crumbs together.
Combine with powdered sugar; mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Melt paraffin wax and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture.
If using candy molds, place small amount of chocolate mixture in bottom of mold. Place peanut butter ball in mold.
Cover with chocolate.
Chill.

title: blue ribbon potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in 2 inches boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes. In large bowl, whisk oil, lemon juice, parsley, garlic, salt, paprika and cumin.
Mix in tomatoes and onion.
Drain potatoes and add to bowl, toss.
Serve warm or room temperature.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pasta fazzole (figole)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Drain beans; add to saute. Add other ingredients and simmer.
Serve over small pasta.

title: chicken or turkey soup
directions: Cover turkey or chicken with water.
Add whole onion and slowly boil until meat is tender.
Remove meat and drain juice through a strainer to remove any bones.
Return juice to pan with onion.

title: layered strawberry dessert
directions: Combine
the crushed crackers and butter; press into an 8-inch square
pan.
Chill.
Combine the cream cheese, sugar, milk
and flavoring.	Spread over the cracker crust.	Arrange the strawberry halves
on
top.
Beat the instant pudding mix with the
milk. Fold
in the whipped topping.
Spoon over the strawberries and chill until set.

title: edith swihart's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, place in a greased baking dish and bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.
This recipe may be doubled.

title: cream puffs
directions: Place butter and boiling water in saucepan.
Heat until butter melts.
Add flour all at once.
Cook until thick and smooth. Place in large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat 1/2 minute for each.

title: banana pudding(good!)
directions: Add first 4 ingredients together.
Slice bananas.
Layer bananas, wafers and filling in large dish.

title: apple nut muffins
directions: Combine sugar, nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Mix well.
Add milk and butter to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Fold in apples.
Lightly grease 12 muffin tins.
Fill 3/4 full.
Sprinkle with nut mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sinful chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
While cake is warm, punch holes in it with a fork.
