Pour sweetened condensed milk over it.
Then pour caramel over that.
Frost with Cool Whip.
(May freeze.)
When ready to serve, crush 3 Heath bars and sprinkle on top.

title: creamy chocolate sauce
directions: Combine chocolate morsels and half and half in a 1-quart glass measure; microwave at High 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir until smooth.
Spoon marshmallow cream into chocolate mixture.
Microwave at High 45 seconds to 1 minute or until marshmallow cream softens.
Add vanilla; stir with a wire whisk until smooth.
Serve warm over ice cream or pound cake.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: wedding punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add sugar and dissolve.
Add juices and let stand until ready to serve.
Place punch in bowl with block of ice.
Pour ginger ale in just before serving. Yields 100 servings.

title: country living vegetables
directions: Slice okra, onions and potatoes.
Heat 1/2-inch shortening or oil in skillet.
Salt the first 3 vegetables and fry until almost done.
Add tomatoes and cook until done.
Drain.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In medium bowl, combine Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds. Drop dough by heaping tablespoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Combine melted Parkay and garlic powder; brush over tops of warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 to 10 biscuits. The sharper the Cheddar, the more flavorful the biscuit.

title: mother of millions cheese base
directions: Finely grate Parmesan and set aside.
Cream
or mash the three cheeses together in the processor slowly.
Refrigerate, tightly wrapped.
Return to room temperature before using.
Makes 1 pound mix.
Make small balls.
Roll mix in toasted pine nuts or almonds.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix together yeast, warm water and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix salt, Crisco and flour together in large bowl.
Add yeast mixture. Knead until well mixed and not sticky (add a little more flour if needed).
Grease bowl and let dough rise for 20 minutes covered. Press dough into two pizza pans.
Add sauce, cheese and your favorite toppings.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken saltimbocca(italian for "jump in mouth quickly")
directions: Place chicken on cutting board.
Place a piece of clear plastic wrap over chicken.
Working from the center out, pound lightly with meat mallet to 5 x 5-inches.
Remove wrap.
Place a ham slice and half slice of Mozzarella cheese on each cutlet, cutting to fit. Top with some tomato and a dash of sage.
Tuck or fold in sides. Roll up jelly roll style, pressing to seal well.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Dip chicken in butter or margarine, then roll in crumbs.
Place in shallow baking dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
May be frozen after cooking.
Serves 6.

title: quick and easy potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and slice them. Do not peel off the skins.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover potatoes with melted butter and soup mix. Mix well. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix well cranberry sauce with sugar, then add crushed pineapple.
Fold in sliced bananas and Cool Whip.
Freeze and serve in squares.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a 5-quart pot; bring to a full rolling boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour into two greased 13 x 9-inch pans.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes 6 pounds.
Do not substitute sweetened condensed milk for evaporated milk.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Saut chopped onions.
Cut cheese into small pieces.
Melt, then mix with cooked, drained spinach and onions.
Serve in chafing dish with Fritos.

title: tortilla turkey soup
directions: Heat oil in heavy large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and saute until translucent, about 4 minutes.
Add chilies, chili powder, cumin, garlic, oregano and cayenne.
Stir 1 minute.
Mix in stock and tomatoes and their juices.
Bring mixture just to boil.
Add turkey and simmer until cooked, about 3 minutes.
Mix in cilantro.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse (makes 2 cups cooked).
Brown hamburger and add beef soup, tomato soup and water.
Simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.
Add macaroni and cheese.
Mix all well and simmer (low, low heat) with cover on for another 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add oil, egg yolks and carrots.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into first mixture.
Pour into greased tube pan or spider pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours in a tube pan or bake for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours in spider pan.
Add glaze to cake while it is hot.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine the softened cream cheese; mix until well blended. Add other ingredients except the nuts
; mix well and shape into a ball.
Roll ball in chopped nuts and parsley flakes.
Before using, remove from freezer and set out at room temperature for about 1 hour.
Makes 2 cheese balls.

title: baked vegetables au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In pan, saute onion in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Cook about 5 minutes or until transparent.
Cut beans in half, if desired.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine onion, green beans, corn, zucchini and tomato wedges; toss.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil; mix well.
Dot the top with remaining butter after mixing with soup.
Sprinkle edge of casserole with bread cubes, then cheese, and bake 60 minutes or until vegetables are tender and cheese is melted.

title: iowa corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in Dutch oven; add onions and saute. Add potatoes, 2 cups water, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add corn with can liquid and evaporated milk.
Blend 1/2 of water with flour.
Return to stove. Add flour mix, stirring constantly, over medium heat until thickened.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: vegetable pizza appetizer
directions: Spread crescent rolls out in large round pizza pan or a jelly roll pan.
Bake according to package instructions or until browned and dough is thoroughly cooked.
Cool.
Mix Ranch dressing and cream cheese together.
Spread on crescent roll crust.
Sprinkle top with vegetables.
Cut and serve.

title: vegetable dip (low-fat)
directions: Cream cottage cheese and salsa in blender.
Stir in mayonnaise.

title: hot milk cake with broiled nut topping
directions: Beat eggs until thick and light colored. Add sugar gradually; add vanilla. Heat milk and butter on medium low until butter melts; beat into mixture quickly. Add dry ingredients a little at a time, mixing well. Pour into well greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes. Spread hot cake with topping.

title: diabetic pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.
Turn down to 350° until a knife stuck in comes out clean.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix buttermilk and oats together and let soak for 1 hour. Next, mix margarine, egg and brown sugar.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix all ingredients together and put in buttered muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 5 minutes.
Pour batter into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: boursin cheese spread
directions: Bring cream cheese and butter to room temperature and blend well. Add garlic and other ingredients. Chill for at least 24 hours before serving with crusty French bread or crackers. This mixture stores well in refrigerator. Remember, you can make more or less of this Boursin cheese spread by blending the herbs and garlic in larger quantities. Use 1 teaspoon blended herbs, 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup cream cheese.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix butter slightly; beat 2 eggs and mix in cake mix.
Mix well.
Spread into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix well and pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can be topped with Cool Whip.

title: chipper bars
directions: Heat
oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, combine oats, flour, brown
sugar,
butter,
soda and salt.
Beat at medium speed, scraping
bowl
often
until
crumbly, 2 to 3 minutes. Reserve
1 1/2 cups crumb mixture; set aside.	Press remaining crumbs on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In small bowl,
stir together
sweetened
condensed
milk
and
peanut butter.
Pour evenly over crumb mixture in pan; sprinkle with chocolate
chips. Pat
reserved
crumb
mixture into filling. Bake for
to 35 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars. Yields 3 dozen.

title: vegetable confetti bars
directions: Grease 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan.
Flatten rolls in pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese and sour cream by hand until smooth.
Add dressing mix and mix well.
Spread over cool roll.
Press mixed vegetables on top of rolls.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before cutting.
Cut in small portions.

title: spiced applesauce
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and vinegar in saucepan. Stir in applesauce and heat.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Measure Rice Krispies in a bowl and top with peanut butter. Boil Karo syrup and 1 cup sugar for 7 minutes.
Add this mixture to Rice Krispies and peanut butter.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with chocolate chips and microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on high. Stir; microwave 1 1/2 more minutes.
Stir and spread over Rice Krispies.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Delicious with assorted crackers and chips.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in first 7 ingredients.
Place rice on bottom of casserole.
Add chicken on top of rice.
Mix soup and water together with drippings from pan.
Stir until just beginning to boil and then pour over chicken and rice in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: silver tea cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg and flavoring.
Beat well.
Mix and sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture with orange juice and rind.
The flour makes a stiff mixture. Form the dough in a roll.
Wrap in wax paper and chill thoroughly. Slice and bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(May be placed by teaspoon with a half walnut pressed in center.)

title: congo squares
directions: Beat eggs; cream sugar.
Add oil and then flour.
Dough will be thick and hard to stir.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes in 1 big sheet cake or one 8 x 8-inch for thicker.
Don't forget to grease the pan.

title: apple fritters(apple barn specialty)
directions: Beat egg.
In mixing bowl combine the milk, egg, sugar and melted margarine.
Add orange juice, rind, chopped apple and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir into milk mixture with spoon until blended.
Do not overmix.
Preheat oil in skillet to 350°.
Drop off end of tablespoon into hot oil and fry to golden brown.
Turn so they brown evenly and allow to cool.
They serve them with spicy apple butter at the Apple Barn Restaurant in Pigeon Forge, Tennessee.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Arrange in layers the sausage, potatoes, zucchini, cheese and soup. Add milk. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Mix all above and top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave 7 to 9 minutes and drain.
Arrange in buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish; distribute chicken on top. Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder together. Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese and then cracker crumbs on top.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or in microwave oven on High for 8 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix well the cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and oranges.
Add marshmallows, bananas and strawberries. Refrigerate.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill well before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: butter balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Leave butter out to soften.
Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes (or until bottoms are lightly browned).
Roll in powdered sugar when fully cool.

title: cranberry frozen salad
directions: Soften cheese.
Blend in mayonnaise and sugar.
Add fruits and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Freeze.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Makes 65 to 80 balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or longer.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt together margarine and Velveeta cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread out into two 9 x 13-inch greased pans.

title: vaca frita(fried cow)
directions: Cook brisket in pressure cooker or on stove top as with a pot roast.
For the liquid, add Vino Seco and enough water to cover meat.
Add to liquid an onion, cut in eighths, the bay leaf, garlic and 2 packets Goya seasoning.
Cook until the brisket shreds.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple in pan and spread.
Dump cherry pie filling and spread.
Dump cake mix over fruit and spread.
Sprinkle with nuts. Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles.
Drain.
Brown ground beef and onion. Add salt, Prego and tomato sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Then simmer. Pour 1/3 sauce in large baking pan.
Lay 3 noodles on top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Spread with 1/3 more sauce, 3 noodles and Parmesan cheese.
Top with rest of sauce and sprinkle again with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven and bake until cheese melts.

title: dad's sweet pepper relish
directions: Remove seeds and chop peppers or grind them through a food grinder.
Soak in brine for 2 or 3 hours or longer.
Drain, then add onions chopped or ground in a similar manner.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain; add vinegar, salt and sugar.
It is improved by the use of pickle spices heated in the bag with the vinegar and by horseradish, either ground or in pieces.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pack in sterile jars and seal.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato sauce & brown sugar. Shape into 4 oz. balls.
Place in a shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: granny's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix on low speed in boiler, eggs and sugar, until well blended.
Blend in both cans of Pet milk.
Continue stirring over medium-high heat until almost boiling.
Pour this mixture into ice cream freezer container.
Add whole milk and fill to line or top of container.
Add vanilla.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Combine butter, onion and celery in 2-quart casserole. Microwave 3 to 4 minutes on High, or until onion is transparent. Add rice, parsley, salt, pepper, bay leaf, thyme, broth and water. Cover; microwave 5 to 6 minutes on High, or until mixture begins to boil.
Reduce setting to "5"; microwave 16 to 18 minutes or until rice is tender.
Let stand, covered, for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: white chocolate chunk brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine brownie mix, eggs, oil and water in a large mixing bowl; blend well.
Fold in white chocolate and walnuts.
Spread batter into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 28 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate morsels over hot brownies.
Return to oven for 1 minute.
Cool before cutting.
tags: Martha White chewy fudge brownie mix

title: potato salad for a crowd
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm, then add Miracle Whip.
Add remaining ingredients and blend with wire whisk.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Boil potatoes with skins on. When cooled, peel and cube.
Add eggs to potatoes and mix with dressing.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
(I cut this recipe in half as it makes a large batch.)

title: rosy rhubarb cake
directions: Blend with fork as for a pie crust the softened butter or oleo, brown sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add beaten egg and milk.
Mixture will be moist.
Spread in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan and up the sides.
Next, spread diced rhubarb over dough.
Then spread Jell-O over rhubarb.
In a small bowl, blend 6 tablespoons butter or oleo, 1 1/2 cups white sugar and 1/2 cup flour.
Sprinkle over rhubarb and Jell-O.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: terri's favorite tuna bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles and drain.
Add tuna and mushroom soup to noodles; mix.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish. You may want to spray with Pam.
Bake approximately 20 minutes.

title: ham sandwiches
directions: Melt oleo and add other ingredients, mixing well.
Chill to spreading consistency.
Split hamburg rolls and spread each side fairly generously with the sauce.
Top with baked, thinly sliced ham and thinly sliced Swiss cheese.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: indonesian pork roast
directions: Brown pork on all sides.
Combine all ingredients and pour over the pork. Simmer 4 hours.
Skim fat or refrigerate overnight and remove fat.
Thicken sauce with cornstarch.
Parboil won bok. Place sliced pork over won bok and pour thickened sauce over before serving.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a covered pan, boil chicken breast on medium heat for 30 minutes.
Save broth to use later.
Cook rice according to the package directions.
In regular casserole dish, mix onion, soup, rice, and chicken.
Add 1 1/2 cup of broth.
Mix well.
Sprinkle pepper on top.
Cook at 350° for 35-45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Dribble 1/3 cup of margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon-pepper wings
directions: Cut wing tips, cut at joint to make winglets.
Combine all ingredients (except wings) in saucepan and simmer 10 minutes. Cool this sauce.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Line a pan with foil and arrange winglets in pan.
Pour sauce over wings and toss.
Bake 25 minutes until golden.

title: cheddar cheese fondue
directions: Combine flour and mustard in fondue pot; set at simmer.
Add half and half gradually; stir until thickened.
Add shredded cheese, 1/4 cup at a time.
Stir until melted.
Add Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce, heat 5 minutes.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Lightly season chicken with salt and pepper; brown slowly in margarine in skillet.
Arrange chicken, skin side up, in baking dish.
Add soup to drippings in skillet.
Slowly add Sauterne, stirring until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover with foil; bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Uncover; continue baking for 25 to 35 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Serve with rice.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Add sugar, salt and 3 cups flour.
Beat 2 minutes and add egg and oil. Gradually beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate up to 3 days.
Punch down.
Form into rolls, pizza dough, cinnamon rolls, etc.
Let rise 1 hour.
Pizza dough does not need to rise.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Yield:
3 to 4 dozen medium rolls or cinnamon rolls, 2 pizzas.

title: oreo delight
directions: In a large bowl, let ice cream soften slightly.
Fold in Cool Whip and coarsely crumbled Oreo cookies.
Pour into pan and return to freezer until ready to serve.

title: dressing
directions: In your
dishes
(buttered),
break store bread (not home baked) and 6 eggs to
each
dish.
Beat.
Add
creamy
milk, salt to taste and pepper if you wish.
I
use
very little.
Pour over bread; do not have too dry.
Dot
with
butter.
Now ready for the oven---"Ummy".
You can use salsify or corn instead of plain.
All three is fit to eat.
Serves 20.

title: perfect pecan pie
directions: Make the best pie pastry recipe. Halve recipe to make one pie pastry. Heat oven to 375°. On a lightly floured work surface, roll out the dough and fit pastry into 9-inch pie pan and flute or crimp the edges.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: Brown pork chops in shortening and drain off the fat.
Mix chicken soup, milk and water; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over the pork chops.
Cover and cook one hour on low heat.
Stir now and then.

title: glazed carrots
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter; add all other ingredients. Pour into baking dish.
Let bake 15 or 20 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, cracker crumbs and butter; roll in small balls.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Dip in 6 or 7 melted Hershey bars in pot with 1/2 cake paraffin wax.

title: my favorite easy five cup salad
directions: Put all together in a bowl, mix and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and Bisquick.
Water may be added if mixture is too dry.
Form into small balls.
Sprinkle with celery salt.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Enjoy!

title: egg salad
directions: Use pastry blender to chop up eggs; mix with mayonnaise, salt and pepper.

title: burning bushes(appetizer)
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Blend all ingredients except dried beef to form a smooth paste.
Arrange thin slices of dried beef on a breadboard to form single five or six inch square layers.
Pieces will have to overlap to form continuous piece. Spread beef slices with cheese mixture and roll up as a jelly roll. Roll should be an inch or so in diameter.
Wrap in moisture vaporproof paper and chill for several hours.
Slice in 3/4 inch slices.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Saute meat until brown; drain.
In large pot, add all ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Yields 16 one ounce cups.

title: pickled green peppers
directions: Pour over this the boiling vinegar solution.
Seal.
Put in hot bath if you choose.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and water in heavy saucepan.
Bring slowly to 230° or until syrup spins thread.
Add peanuts and continue to cook to 300°.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla, soda and salt and stir until blended.
Pour into 2 well buttered jelly-roll pans (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
As it starts to cool, pull it until thin.
When completely cool, break into pieces. Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: english walnut bread
directions: Into mixing bowl, sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut into shortening.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups of the walnuts. Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix just until ingredients are blended.
Turn into pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup of walnuts over top.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes or until leaf tests done. Let stand in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out onto wire rack to cool. Makes 1 loaf.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix together.
Shape into meatballs.
Bake at 350° for one hour, or until done.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots with salt until nearly done.
Drain and save liquid.
Add margarine, mustard, celery salt, pepper, onion and flour to carrots and stir well until carrots are coated.
To liquid from carrots, add enough milk to make 2 cups (usually about half and half).
Place over low heat and add cheese gradually, stirring as cheese melts.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover with corn flakes. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
May be prepared day ahead and then baked.
Makes about 3 quarts.
Good for community dinners.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve and mix first four ingredients.
Set aside to cool. Mix well all ingredients except flour.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Add flour a little at a time.
Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead until you've used all the flour.
Let rise until double. Punch down.
Make into rolls and place on well oiled pans.
(Rolls can be placed in refrigerator or placed on pans in the freezer and once frozen placed in bags.)
When ready to bake, allow to come to room temperature and rise until double.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Cook and stir meat and onions until meat is brown and onions tender.
Add water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 50 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour meat mixture into ungreased baking dish.
Arrange potatoes on meat.
Stir together soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and cereal. Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes and meat are tender.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients and vanilla. Add apples and pecans. Bake in 11 x 9 pan at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Mix chicken, cream cheese (softened), milk and seasonings to taste.
Divide crescent rolls into triangles; fill with mixture. Fold tops over to form squares.
Brush tops with butter; bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chalet ham dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; add milk slowly.
Serve with Swiss cheese crackers.

title: bread pudding
directions: In double boiler, mix brown sugar, bread and raisins.
Beat together eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour over bread mixture.
Cook 1 hour over boiling water.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: mama's asparagus casserole
directions: Place drained asparagus in bottom of baking dish.
Pour cream of celery soup on top (do not add water to soup).
Toast and butter bread.
Crumble to pieces.
Place on top of asparagus.
Bake at 350° until heated and top is crispy (15 to 20 minutes).

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking dish. Melt margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Add shallots and saute until limp.
Add nuts and chopped mushroom stems and saute an additional 3 minutes.
Mix in bread crumbs, thyme, salt and pepper to taste.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Place in baking dish and bake 15 minutes.

title: mushroom steaks
directions: Add enough water to mushroom juice to make 1/2 cup.
Heat and dissolve butter and Vegex in it.
Mix all ingredients except soup. Fry in patties.
Place fried patties in casserole and cover with can of soup diluted with milk.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Vegex is a meat-like flavoring obtained in health food stores.

title: ham and potato skillet
directions: Slice potatoes; halve any large slices.
In a large skillet, cook potatoes and fresh green beans (if using) in water, covered, about 15 minutes or until potatoes and beans are tender.
(If using frozen beans, add to potatoes the last 5 minutes of cooking.)
Drain well.

title: banana bran bread
directions: In medium mixing bowl, cream oil and sugar, then add egg and bran flakes.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add chopped nuts.
Combine bananas and water; add to creamed mixture alternately with dry.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf or 3 small loaves (bake for 35 minutes for small loaves).

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand milk, lime juice and yellow food coloring (if desired).
Pour into prepared pie shell; bake 30 minutes.
Cool. Chill.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish with lime slices. Refrigerate.

title: hermit cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt together and cream, along with eggs, into shortening.
Cream in brown sugar and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: diabetic pound cake
directions: Measure Bisquick into a large bowl.
Cut in margarine until it is pea size.
Beat in eggs and sweetener until dissolved.
Add vanilla and beat combined ingredients well.
Use greased tube pan or loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in the pan.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Saute garlic, onion and ground beef until brown.
Add spaghetti sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
If desired, add sugar. Simmer and set aside.

title: halloween sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Stir together dry ingredients and blend in.
Divide dough in half.
Chill one hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Using circular cutter, cut out shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° about 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: frosted maple pecan white chip cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking soda in medium bowl. Beat brown sugar, shortening, butter, eggs, maple flavoring and vanilla in large mixer bowl until creamy. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels and chopped pecans. Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheets.

title: ranchero
directions: Combine ground chuck, oil, garlic, salt, rice, onion, green pepper, chili powder and tomatoes; mix in beans last.
Mix well. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°, then top with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: my goulash
directions: Spray Dutch oven with Pam. Saute onion and pepper. Add ground meat which has been seasoned with seasoning salt and black pepper. Cook until all the redness is gone from the meat. Add all other ingredients and while this is cooking, boil about 2 quarts of water. Add noodles and return to a boil. Cook about 5 or 6 minutes. Drain. Fold noodles into the meat mixture. Pour into a buttered, large, oblong Pyrex casserole dish. Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with grated Cheddar (or cheese of your choice) and return to oven for about 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: white trash(snack)
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter in double boiler (or microwave).
Mix peanuts, raisins and cereal in a bowl. Pour chocolate mixture over cereal mixture.
Pour half the sugar into a large bag.
Add half the cereal mixture; shake to coat. Repeat with the remaining cereal.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or just until set. Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet and cool completely.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread crescent rolls into baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 6 minutes. Add fried, drained sausage, thawed hash browns, and eggs. Bake for 25 minutes. Top with cheese. Bake another 5 minutes until cheese browns lightly.

title: crawfish etouffe
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic in butter until cooked down.
Add tomato paste and flour.
Cook down.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup water.
Add uncooked crawfish and let cook for 20-30 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Cook for another 20-30 minutes on low.
If too thick add some water.
Stir and eat.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Mix milk, 2 cups sugar and butter.
Cook mixture to a soft ball stage, then brown 1 cup sugar until it completely melts. Pour into hot mixture; beat.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: pumpkin-apple streusel muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl and set aside.
Combine eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Add to first mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Add chopped apples and mix.
Spoon batter into greased or paper-lined muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
In small bowl, mix flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick gazpacho
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Store covered and chilled for 4 days before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar,
carrots
and oil together.
Add 1 egg at a time and
beat.	Add
cinnamon,	flour and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In food processor bowl, add tomatoes, garlic, onion, chili powder, cumin, oregano and sugar.
Process until smooth.
Reserve 2/3 of mixture for later.
In food processor with remaining 1/3 of sauce, add chicken and process until lightly shredded.
Lightly grease a large, oblong baking dish.

title: mattee's oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together water, oatmeal and oleo; let stand.
Mix sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Add flour, cinnamon, soda, vanilla, nutmeg, pecans and coconut.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat the eggs and sugar together.
Add margarine and syrup. Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: salad dressing
directions: Whisk together and pour over spring salad mix. Top with roasted almonds and eat to your heart's content.

title: energizing vitamin and fruit smoothie
directions: In blender, combine banana, pineapple and honey.
Blend until smooth.
Add orange juice, yogurt and ice; blend until combined and mixture is thick and creamy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: popeye's biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, sour cream and soda.
Put 1/2 butter or margarine in baking pan and melt.
Use plain flour to hand make or hand roll biscuits.
Put into buttered pan and bake at 425°.
Add other 1/2 stick of margarine.

title: mexican style baked turkey loaf
directions: Saute the onion, celery and bell peppers in a small amount of olive oil until just cooked through, but not translucent.
Cool.

title: gobs
directions: Combine flour and milk in shaker and shake until flour is dissolved.
Pour into saucepan and bring to desired thickness over low heat, constantly stirring.
Cool slightly.
Combine shortening with flour mixture.
Add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla.
Beat on high speed until fluffy.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans; next day rinse thoroughly.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover with enough water.
Can cook in crock-pot or oven at 375° until beans are tender.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O by directions.
Add other ingredients; mix well. Put in refrigerator until congealed.
Serve on lettuce leaves topped with mayonnaise.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Combine marshmallows, evaporated milk and orange juice in small bowl and set aside.
In large bowl, combine graham crackers crumbs and spices; mix well.
Stir in coconut, fruits and nuts. Add liquid mixture; press together until moist and sticky.
Press into large glass pan.
Cover with foil (tightly) and keep refrigerated.
(May be frozen.)

title: noodle casserole
directions: While noodles are cooking, make white sauce of margarine, flour and milk.
Add grated cheese, Soyameat and mushrooms.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly and well heated.

title: yummy party sausage
directions: Boil sausage to degrease it, then cut into 1/4 to 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Place in uncovered casserole and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: grandma's muffins
directions: Mix all well.
Place in muffin tins. Bake 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar.
Sift together all dry ingredients and add to eggs and sugar.
Beat to blend.
Add zucchini and nuts. Bake in a 10-inch tube pan, greased and floured, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda, spices and salt together. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, molasses and milk, mixing well.
Add dry ingredients; beat until smooth. Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan; bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lo-cal bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix cereal, flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. Add eggs, buttermilk and Butter Buds and mix well.
Spray muffin tins with Pam.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake at 400°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes and paste.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: cranberry walnut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all dry ingredients. In a food processor, process all wet ingredients until smooth. Add liquid mixture to dry and mix well. Pour batter into lightly oiled 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool. Cut into squares and serve.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Yields 1 quart.

title: tomatoed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato.
Mix well and cook over medium heat until margarine is melted.
Cover and continue to cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in tomato.
Cover and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: apricot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add jar of sauce and set aside. Cook and drain spaghetti. Mix 1/2 of sauce mixture with spaghetti and put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Saute green pepper and onion in butter. Add cream cheese and enough milk to make it smooth. Then spread over spaghetti. Pour remaining sauce over cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes and top with fried onions. Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter roll(old fashioned potato candy)
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat. Stir in evaporated milk, vanilla and salt. Remove from heat and gradually add the powdered sugar.

Turn out on waxed paper, lightly sprinkled with powdered sugar, and work with hands until smooth. Roll out in oblong shape. Cover with peanut butter. Start at side and roll up to other side. Wrap in waxed paper and freeze. When hard, take out and slice.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and chicken; put in casserole.
Moisten stuffing with water or leftover juice and margarine.
Pour on top of first mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red cabbage
directions: Shred red cabbage. Saut onion in margarine. Add cabbage, bay leaves, cloves, apple, vinegar and sugar. Cover (barely) with water and cook for about 20 minutes until soft.

title: carrot bars
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix all together.
Bake for 25 minutes or more on cookie sheet at 350°.

title: iced lemon tea
directions: Boil water, sugar and lemon peel together for 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice, tea, almond extract and vanilla.
Cool and serve over ice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip and orange jello.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate several hours.

title: ham delights
directions: Slice entire package of rolls in half across.
Place margarine in mixer and add mustard, onion and poppy seed.
Mix well.
Spread rolls on both sides with spread.
Place thinly sliced ham on top of spread.
Put Swiss cheese (or your choice of cheese) on top of ham.
Put roll tops on and place back in pans; cover with foil and freeze.
When ready to serve, cook at 350° for 20 minutes (30 minutes if frozen).
Take from oven and cut into rolls.

title: chicken rotini soup
directions: Combine chicken and water in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer 2 minutes. Drain water and rinse chicken to remove any small white pieces that cook out of chicken.
Saute onion and mushrooms until slightly tender.
Stir in chicken broth, Worcestershire sauce and tarragon.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Stir in uncooked pasta.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Add zucchini to soup.
Simmer, uncovered, about 5 minutes more, or until pasta is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit of narragansett bay(serves 10)
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions and garlic until golden; add wine. Add shellfish and juices.
Done when shells open.
In boiling water, cook linguine.
Rinse and toss in butter, parsley, salt and pepper.
Arrange linguine on platter.
Pour shellfish sauce over linguine.
Serve with crusty bread and green salad.

title: microwave caramels
directions: Melt butter; blend in brown sugar, condensed milk, salt and corn syrup.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave 10 minutes on High.
Stir 2 or 3 times.
Microwave, uncovered, 13 to 20 minutes on Medium-high.

title: gloria's chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Mix egg and bread crumbs together.
Dip chicken pieces into egg mixture.
Saute in butter. Place in baking dish.
Mix in mushrooms.
Cover with sliced cheese and soup.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: oven fried apples
directions: Fill a large casserole
dish
(13 x 9-inch) with sliced apples (do not peel).
Sprinkle sugar over apples and dot with margarine. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with aluminum foil. Take a toothpick and punch a
lot
of
holes
in
the aluminum foil. Do not add any water.
Bake
at
oven
for
1/2 hours.

title: stir-fry bologna
directions: Cook the rice until it is done, then add the green beans, peas and bologna.
Add the soy sauce.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Bake in a 350° oven until meat falls off bone.
Cut up in small pieces.
Put in bowl you can chop it up in.
Add sauce, salt and pepper. Mix together and add rest of ingredients. Simmer about 1 hour, stirring occasionally to make sure it doesn't stick.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a Bundt pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: red clam sauce (for pasta)(serves 4)
directions: Chop clams; save juice.
In a heavy saucepan, saute the garlic in the oil for 1 minute, but do not let the garlic brown.
Add the parsley, tomatoes and their juice, tomato paste and 1/2 cup of the clam juice.
Simmer the sauce, uncovered, for about 40 minutes or until the sauce is thickened.
Add the clams, oregano and pepper and simmer the sauce 2 minutes longer.
Serve.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Mix sugar, milk and flour together and pour over margarine.
Pour peaches, juice and all, over batter and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: brie with wild mushrooms
directions: Soak mushrooms in 1 1/2 cups water for 1 hour.
Strain liquid through cheesecloth.
Reserve.
Rinse mushrooms twice in bowl of cold water.
Squeeze dry.
Chop and set aside.
Saute shallots in butter until translucent.
Add mushrooms and soaking liquid.
Boil until liquid evaporates.
Add tarragon, salt and pepper.
Chill. Cut Brie into two layers.
Spread bottom layer with creme fraiche. Top with mushrooms.
Re-sandwich, wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate 1 to 3 days.
Serve at room temperature with crackers. Serves about 10 to 12.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients in this order:
oil, eggs, apples, vanilla and pecans.
Beat well and bake in tube pan for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put sliced apples in baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and pour the honey over.
Mix flour, brown sugar, salt and butter into crumbs.
Put on top of apples and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 375° oven until apples are tender.

title: penney's raspberry cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 9-inch spring-form pan. Lightly spoon flour in measuring cup and level off.

title: chicken and chips
directions: Combine chicken, celery, 1/2 cup cheese, olives, onions, salt and enough mayonnaise or salad dressing to moisten; toss lightly. Place in a casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and chips. Garnish with tomato wedges.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, marshmallow cream and milk and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into greased pan.
Cool.

title: cranberry sour cream jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix sour cream into mixture with beater or wire whip until smooth.
Add cranberries, nuts and lemon.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in large skillet (T-Fal works great), just enough oil to cover bottom.
Coat sliced tomatoes in cornmeal, flour, cheese mixture. Fry over medium/high heat until brown on both sides.
Drain well on paper towels.

title: hungry jack coffee cake
directions: Melt margarine and coat bottom and sides of tube pan with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons nuts on bottom of pan.
Add remaining nuts, brown sugar and water to remaining margarine and boil.
Cut biscuits in half and roll into balls. Place 1/2 biscuits in pan and pour 1/2 caramel sauce over.
Then repeat with remaining biscuits and caramel sauce.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Invert immediately.

title: ruby relish
directions: Wash cranberries and combine with sugar and V-8 juice in saucepan.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cook over low heat until cranberries pop.
Chill.
Before serving, stir in pineapple.
The best cranberry sauce you can find.

title: linguine with tomatoes and shrimp
directions: Melt butter with oil in a large, heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook until soft, stirring, about 8 minutes.
Add tomatoes and the next 5 ingredients to skillet. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook until tomatoes are soft, about 6 minutes.
Add shrimp; stir until heated through.
Add 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese; pour over pasta and toss.
Serve immediately. Pass remaining Parmesan, separately.

title: vegetarian spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl, then spread on fresh bread for great sandwiches.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet.
In a large Dutch oven, warm milk and add bread, poultry seasoning and eggs.
Add meat when done. Either stuff turkey or put in casserole dish.
Enjoy!

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach per package directions.
Drain well.
In saucepan over low heat, mix together cheese, milk, margarine and nutmeg. Cook until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat and stir in the spinach, half of the bacon and the lemon juice.
Turn mixture into serving dish and sprinkle with remaining bacon.

title: pineapple angel food
directions: Combine cake mix and undrained pineapple in a large bowl, stirring until well blended. Pour into a 9 x 11 ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: beth's pot roast meat loaf
directions: Peel and slice (1/4-inch thick) the vegetables.
Mix dried parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Place vegetables in layers around the meat loaf.
Sprinkle each layer with a part of the salt mixture.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour, or until vegetables are tender.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer to brown meat.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil together brown sugar, white sugar and milk for 5 minutes. Have ready and mixed the Marshmallow Fluff, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts (optional).
Pour together boiled sugar into peanut butter mixture and spread into a greased pan.

title: yummy chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch with eggs yolks.
Add milk a little at a time.
Stir until well mixed.
Add butter. At low-medium heat, bring to a boil stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into browned pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 300 degrees until brown.

title: cream cheese puff
directions: Put vanilla wafer in bottom of aluminum foil baking cup.
Fill 3/4 full with mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Immediately top with cherry pie filling.
Chill.

title: toffee-like candy
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Layer saltines on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Boil butter and sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over saltines and bake for 7 minutes.
(Watch carefully.)
Remove from oven and spread chocolate bits over top of saltines.
Don't let it cool and do it on open oven door so the syrup on the cracker is liquid hot. Cool in refrigerator.
Break into pieces before serving.

title: "easy ice cream"
directions: Combine in a sandwich size plastic bag. Seal the "Ziploc" bag so there is a minimal amount of air trapped inside the bag. Shake the bag for 5 seconds to blend the contents. Place the sandwich bag in a gallon size plastic bag that is halfway full of ice. Add 1/3 cup of table salt or rock salt to the gallon bag. Seal the "Ziploc" gallon bag. Shake and/or roll the gallon bag on a table until the mixture reaches the consistency of Dairy Queen ice cream, approximately 10 minutes. Remove the sandwich bag. Rinse the sandwich bag in cold water until the salt is removed from the outside of the bag. Eat and enjoy the ice cream.

title: dump peach cobbler
directions: Grease 2-quart oblong casserole dish.
Dump ingredients, just as they are listed and do not mix until vanilla is added and then mix well. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until top is golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: In a large soup pot, boil the potatoes; drain, season and mash potatoes.
Add sour cream, cream cheese and onion; mix thoroughly. Place in 2-quart casserole dish and allow to cool.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Top with melted butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a 2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Prepare mashed potatoes according to package directions using water, skim milk and diet margarine (omit salt called for on package).
Set aside.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup of pecans. Mix well. Roll cheese ball in the 1/2 cup of pecans or mold cheese ball on the serving dish and sprinkle pecans on top and around the sides.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix strawberries, eggs, oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients into berry mixture.
Stir to blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and pour into 3 medium loaf pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Cut sausage into small pieces and fry until lightly browned, stirring constantly.
Add water.
Combine cracker crumbs, rice, tomatoes, pepper and onion.
Mix lightly.
Add sausage.
Turn into greased casserole and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend ingredients; pour into pie crust.
Chill.

title: mama's crab meat imperial
directions: Heat in a double boiler.
Serve with Melba toast as dip.

title: bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon, beef and onion; drain.
Transfer to greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add all beans and other ingredients and mix well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: In a skillet, fry bacon until crisp, then put bacon on paper towel to drain.
Add ground beef and onion to drippings in skillet.
Cook until ground beef is brown and crumbly.
Add bread cubes, ketchup, chili powder and pepper.
Mix well and set aside.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In skillet or wok, cook chicken in 2 tablespoons oil until tender.
Mix together broccoli, cauliflower, celery, onions, bell peppers and cabbage.
Pour into skillet with chicken.
Add stir-fry mix and let simmer until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Combine Tang, sugar, instant tea, spices and salt.
Makes 2 cups dry mix or enough for 6 quarts of tea.

title: hash brown quiche(serves 6)
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press hash browns into pan.
Pour butter over hash browns.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 425°. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with ham, onions and cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk and pour over top.
May also add mushrooms.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Melt margarine and add to oats.
Sift sugar, flour and baking powder together and add to oats.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add vanilla and add both to the oat mixture.
Add chopped pecans (optional).

title: chip dip
directions: Gradually combine all ingredients, in a blender or by hand, adding enough milk to keep thick, but smooth.
If necessary, add more onion, garlic and horseradish to taste.

title: salad with a multitude of sins
directions: Drain pineapple and save the juice.
Combine the juice with enough of the boiling water to equal two cups of liquid.
Add lime Jell-O and marshmallows and stir until Jell-O is dissolved and marshmallows are melted.
Chill mixture until it begins to thicken.
Next, add cheese, celery, pineapple, nuts and lemon juice.
Combine Cool Whip and salad dressing and add to the mixture.
Pour into mold or serving bowl and refrigerate for at least 12 hours.

title: sour cream sauce for veggies
directions: In small pan melt butter.
Saute onion.
Remove from heat and stir in all remaining ingredients.
Excellent over broccoli, green beans, asparagus or peas.
If any leftovers, keep in refrigerator. Then to use again, just reheat to serving temperature.
Don't boil.

title: kuftehs(meat balls)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomatoes, until well blended. Form meat mixture into 2-inch size balls (may need a bit more flour to help the balls to hold together).
Brown the balls in olive oil on medium heat using a nonstick skillet.
Carefully place the meat balls in a medium saucepan; add tomatoes.
Cover and simmer on low for 10 minutes.
Tastes great served with pita bread toast.

title: heavenly hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in microwave or double boiler. Gradually stir in the sugar, 4 tablespoons at a time, being sure the sugar is completely moistened after each addition.
The mixture will be very thick and quite dry.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and evaporated milk.
Add milk slowly and stir until it is a satiny smooth sauce.
Do not boil!
Add vanilla.
Sauce will be thick and if you desire a thinner sauce, stir in an additional tablespoon or two of milk.
Keep refrigerated.

title: greek lemon soup
directions: Place stock in a medium-size heavy bottom saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add rice and reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook until tender, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: country captain chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine rice and raisins in shallow 13 x 9-inch dish.
Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Stir in curry. Add chicken and brown well on all sides.
Arrange on rice mixture.
Add water, tomato sauce, salt and Worcestershire sauce to drippings in skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken. Cover and bake for 40 to 45 minutes until chicken is tender. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, pepper, rice, eggs and salt and garlic to taste in large bowl.
Roll into large meatballs (about the size of the palm of your hand).
Brown in large saucepan until meatballs are done, stirring often.
Drain off grease; add tomato sauce.
Add 1 can of water.
Cook on low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Leave in sauce.

title: broccoli squares
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add beaten eggs and milk. Mix well, then blend in all other ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sunday hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix yeast, sugar, eggs and warm water.
Add oil, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Let stand 8 hours or overnight.
Do not refrigerate.
Shape into rolls or loaf.
Should be ready to bake by lunch.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: hot cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage rather fine.
Put in saucepan and sprinkle with salt.
Cover pan and place over low heat.
Steam until very tender.
Beat the egg; add the sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar. Pour over the steamed cabbage.
Heat for 5 minutes.
Serve at once.
Serves 8.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Spread this mixture on both sides of hamburger bun.
Layer with meat and cheese.
Wrap in foil. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 9 to 10 sandwiches.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin and water in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan until gelatin is dissolved.
Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Mix well. Refrigerate until set.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in butter until golden.
Blend in flour and seasonings; cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat; gradually add milk.
Bring to boil; boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add corn and egg.
Pour into a 1-quart baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fiesta siesta chili
directions: Brown meats in a skillet; reserve, discarding fat.
Heat oil in a heavy pot over low heat; cook onions, garlic and bell peppers for 15 minutes or until tender.
Stir in the next 9 ingredients; cook 2 to 3 minutes to forge the flavors together.
Add jalapenos, tomatoes, tomato sauce and reserved meats.
Heat through and simmer for 15 minutes.
Season to taste.
Serves 8.

title: southern biscuit muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk until flour mixture is moistened.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add meringue, return to oven until top is brown.

title: crab delight
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve in hot soup.
Cool. Beat in cheese and add all other ingredients.
Pour into mold that has been lightly coated with salad oil or Pam.
Refrigerate overnight.
Turn out on a bed of lettuce.
A fish mold makes a very attractive dish.
For heavy hors d'oeuvres.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 20.

title: orange pecans
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and orange juice in a saucepan; mix well. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mixture reaches soft-ball stage (240°). Remove from heat; stir in butter. Beat with a wooden spoon until mixture just begins to thicken. Stir in pecans and orange rind. Working rapidly, drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool. Yield: 1 1/4 dozen.

title: sunday soup supper
directions: Meatballs:
In medium bowl, combine beef, egg, 3 tablespoons water, bread crumbs, salt and 1 tablespoon parsley.
Mix by hand until well combined.
Shape into balls.
Brown in butter in a 5-quart Dutch oven, one layer at a time.
Set aside.
Drain fat.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugars and oleo together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake.

title: spicy kisses
directions: Beat egg white with salt until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar mixed with spices.
Fold in nuts.
Drop from teaspoonful onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Top with walnut halves.
Bake at 250° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apples and oatmeal
directions: Mix in baking dish apple pie filling, lemon juice and cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine oatmeal, brown sugar and margarine.
Distribute mixture over apples.

title: lovefeast buns
directions: In a large saucepan, melt shortening and then add milk and sugar.
Heat carefully.
Prepare yeast.
Add potatoes to hot mixture.
Add hot mixture to flour in large bowl.
Add eggs.
Mix and then add yeast mixture.
Let rise in a warm place until double the bulk.
Make buns and dip into melted butter and then brown sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit compote
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving the juice.
In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 minute more. Remove from heat. Set aside.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown
ground
meat; set aside to drain.
Mix cornbread batter up and pour 1/3 into heated Dutch oven.
Return ground meat to skillet and add taco seasoning, follow instructions on package. Cook until all water is gone.
Place ground meat mix on top of batter in Dutch oven, being careful not to go to the edge
of batter.
Place
bell pepper and onions and pour corn over everything, being careful not to touch of batter.
Place thick sliced
cheese
on	top.
Pour
remaining
batter
over everything.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix can of lemonade, Cool Whip, condensed milk and lemon juice together with beater.
Pour in graham cracker pie crust and chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add egg and beat with a fork.
Pour over apples and shake down.
Dot with margarine.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly and crust is brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cocoa and milk and cook for 3 minutes. Add butter and stir until melted.
Add vanilla and peanut butter. Beat until cool; pour into buttered dish.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Chill this and other liquids. When ready to serve, pour each over sherbet in punch bowl.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain vegetables completely.
(All cans of vegetables should be the same size.)
Add onions and green peppers.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
(Will keep for days.)

title: pudding for pie
directions: Scald milk.
Mix sugar, flour, egg yolks and small amount of milk.
Pour into scalded milk and cook until thickened.
Take off stove and add oleo, salt and vanilla.
Add coconut or pour over bananas for pie in crust.

title: french baked potatoes
directions: Peel and wash potatoes.
Coat with butter.
Bake in well-oiled pan for 35 minutes at 375°.
Turn at least 3 times during baking.
Remove from oven and roll in crushed cornflakes. Bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: cornstarch pudding
directions: Heat milk in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in slowly rest of ingredients, thinned by adding a little milk or water mixed together to make a paste.
Keep stirring until thick.
Good layered with graham crackers or in baked pie shell.

title: onion bacon bread
directions: Combine onion,
bacon
and
garlic in skillet and saute until golden.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, salt and 2
cups
flour.
Beat
until
well blended.
Stir in undrained onion,
bacon
and
garlic.
Add
enough additional flour to make soft
dough.
Knead
well
and let rise in warm place until doubled.
Punch
down and shape into loaf.
Place in greased 9
x 5-inch
loaf pan.
Cover and let rise about 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done. Makes one 9-inch loaf.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients well and roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: impossible lasagne pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inches). Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan in plate.
Brown beef and drain. Mix beef, herbs, paste and 1/2 of the Mozzarella.
Spoon mixture on top.
Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper for one minute with beater and pour over the top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Top with the rest of the Mozzarella cheese.
Serve with your favorite green salad and enjoy.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup warm water. Add milk and yeast mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Use as needed.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tomato cucumber salad
directions: Put tomatoes, cucumbers, and pepper into a bowl.
Add dill weed, parsley, salt and pepper.
Squeeze juice of 2 limes over top of salad and mix.
Great for barbecues and easy!

title: mary todd lincoln's white cake recipe
directions: Cream sugar, butter and vanilla.
Sift together cake flour and baking powder three times.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in almonds.
Gently fold in the egg whites.
Pour into two greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix biscuits that have each been quartered, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Make sure biscuits are coated. On top of stove, melt stick of margarine, 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Place half of biscuit mix in greased (with nonstick spray) Bundt pan.
Pour 1/2 melted mixture over.
Add remainder of biscuits, then remainder of mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Turn upside down and lift off pan.

title: fruit and nut compote
directions: In a 9 x 11-inch cake pan, layer the apple pie filling, first, then top evenly with the drained pineapple, then sprinkle the yellow cake mix (dry) over it.
Melt and drizzle the melted margarine over the cake mix and top with the chopped walnuts. Bake at 350°
for approximately 50 minutes.
Serve warm over vanilla ice cream or serve warm and top with whipped cream.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, and blend well. Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk. Add vanilla. Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Cook rice a little on top of stove first.
Then mix with other ingredients in a casserole dish and bake at 325° to 350° for about 1 hour.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Fill jars with quartered, unpeeled cucumbers.
Mix together salt, mustard, vinegar and water and pour over cucumbers.
Seal tight.
Leave in refrigerator for two weeks before storing.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook in casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt all together. Make a well in center of mixture and pour in milk and egg. Mix until smooth. Using a funnel, fill with batter and hold over very hot oil. Let the batter fall in circle motion. If using Fry Daddy make it the size of the Fry Daddy. If you use a pan, try to make it the size of your plates. Fry on each side until golden brown, about 2 minutes on each side. Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: honey mustard
directions: Combine all ingredients and season to taste with white pepper. Makes 2 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish or put apple pie filling in dish.
If using apples, sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add egg; mix until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Pour melted oleo over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: cajun quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Combine mayonnaise, flour, milk and eggs; mix well. Stir in crabmeat and shrimp. Add cheese and green onions. Pour mixture into pie shell; bake 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Pour cider into large pot.
Add spices and bring to a boil. Turn heat down.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: fruit whip delight
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: big sister's harvard beets
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: easy gazpacho soup
directions: Seed, peel and chop tomatoes.
Chop Vidalia onion, green pepper and cucumbers.
Mince garlic.
Remove crusts from bread and tear in pieces.
Combine tomatoes, onion, bell pepper, cucumbers, garlic, bread and basil in a large bowl.
(Two teaspoons of dried basil can be substituted for fresh basil.)
Mix well and let stand for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Transfer mixture in batches, if necessary, to an electric blender container or food processor bowl fitted with a steel chopping blade.
Process just until no large pieces remain.
Do not puree, mixture should have texture.
Return mixture to bowl, stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight for flavors to blend.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut up broccoli.
Steam broccoli.
Mix broccoli and Cheddar cheese together.
One roll crackers mixed together with 1/2 stick butter.
Bake 25 minutes or microwave 10 to 15 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix mashed artichokes with mayonnaise. Fold in Parmesan cheese.
Put in small casserole dish and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Spray cooking spray in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pineapple and juice in bottom of pan.
Add 1 can cherry pie filling on pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over the fruit.
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and pumpkin.
Add all other dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a 2-quart glass container, combine sugar, butter and milk. Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes or until sugar is dissolved, stirring twice.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until chocolate pieces are melted and cream is well blended.
Turn into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Chill until firm.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: In saucepan, combine celery, potato, onion, 1 cup water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add milk and flour; stir into potato mixture.
Add shrimp and butter.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: southern cornbread dressing with giblet gravy
directions: Cook giblets in enough water to cover until tender.
Chop and set aside.
Heat broth and season.
Stir a little milk gradually into flour or cornstarch until smooth.
Add a little hot broth to this; stir until fairly thin and return to pot.
Simmer until a nice consistency (not too thick).
Add hard-boiled egg and giblets. Serve in gravy boat.

title: poultry casserole
directions: Simmer for 45 minutes and debone (leave quail whole).
Place meat in baking dish; salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff quail with favorite dressing if desired.
(I use sausage and bread crumbs moistened with chicken stock.)
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream and spread over meat.
Melt butter and drizzle over sauce. Crush Ritz crackers; sprinkle over sauce.
Add poppy or sesame seed over all.
If desired, white wine or sherry may be added to sauce initially.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix and allow to sit 15 to 30 minutes.
Mix again.
Press firmly into a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Lightly salt chicken. Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix together chopped celery, soup, mayonnaise and drained water chestnuts.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle generously with the cornbread crumbs.
Melt margarine and pour over crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan, over medium heat, melt chocolate chips and butter with sweetened condensed milk, water and vanilla.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Serve over ice cream or cream puffs.
Refrigerate leftover sauce.

title: russian tea
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 1 hour and strain.

title: crabmeat imperial
directions: Beat mayonnaise, eggs, Tabasco sauce, lemon juice and salt. Fold in crabmeat.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot top with butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Cook 3 cups of peaches with 1/4 cup of sugar until mixture comes to a boil.
Add remaining sugar, butter, salt and cornstarch. Cook until clear and glossy.
Place remaining peaches in pastry shell.
Pour hot mixture of peaches.
Let cool.
Enjoy.

title: broccoli amandine
directions: Scrub potatoes well.
Dry, then prick with a fork.
Bake at 425° for 55 to 60 minutes, until soft.
In medium saucepan, heat oil; saute onion and garlic until tender.
Add broccoli, chicken broth and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, until broccoli is crisp-tender.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice medium thin.
Make a white sauce of butter, flour, salt and milk.
When thickened, remove from stove and add grated cheese.
Stir cheese into sauce.
Place sliced potatoes in a 3-quart casserole.
Cover with hot white sauce and bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 1/2 hours after covering mixture with buttered bread crumbs.

title: maplely appetizers
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Cut sausage into thirds and brown.
Blend cornstarch, salt, maple syrup and pineapple syrup, water and vinegar.
Heat to boil; reduce temperature and simmer until thick.
Add pineapple, sausage, green pepper and cherries. Heat thoroughly and serve from fondue pot.

title: kurt's grilled lamb
directions: Place meat in a glass roasting pan.
Distribute onion rings over meat.
Combine vinegar, honey, oil and dry mustard to blend. Pour over lamb and onion and marinate in the refrigerator at least 24 hours, turning occasionally.
Let stand at room temperature one hour before grilling.
Place onion on a foil square and fashion into a pouch.
Grill meat over medium-hot coals until desired doneness (about 40 minutes for medium).
Place onion packet at edge of coals to heat through and become soft but not brown. Slice meat onto a heated plater; top with onion rings and ladle some of the warmed marinade over.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil in large skillet until well browned.
Add peppers and onions; cook until just soft, still a little crisp.
Mix cornstarch and soy sauce.
Add to pan with pineapple and juice, vinegar, sugar, ginger and garlic powder. Bring to a full boil.
Meanwhile, prepare rice as directed on package.
Serve over rice.

title: aunt lydia's cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
In seperate bowl, cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and buttermilk, mix in flour mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto baking sheet and bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes.

title: pink fluffy cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Let stand 2 hours.
Combine cranberry mixture, whipped cream and marshmallows; fold in pineapple, apples or grapes.
Will keep in fridge several days.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Saute in 1/2 stick margarine the onions and zucchini together. Mix remaining margarine with stuffing.
Mix soup, sour cream and carrots together.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a crock pot. Let simmer. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: country club turkey
directions: Drain asparagus thoroughly.
Place in greased shallow baking dish.
Cut olives into large pieces.
Combine with soup, onion, rosemary and turkey; pour over asparagus.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peach dumplings
directions: Combine peaches, water, sugar and lemon juice in a 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil.
(If using canned fruit, use 2/3 cup sugar and fruit juice instead of water.)
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Stir lightly.
Drop batter from teaspoon on hot mixture.
Reduce heat.
Cover tightly.
Cook 15 minutes without lifting lid.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream or plain.
Any fruit may be used.

title: perfect peppermint patties
directions: In a bowl, combine first 4 ingredients. Add milk and mix well. Roll into 1-inch balls and place on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet. Chill for 20 minutes. Flatten with a glass to 1/4-inch; chill for 30 minutes. Melt chocolate chips and shortening. Dip patties; place on wax paper to harden. Makes 5 dozen.

title: oreo dessert(this dessert is made of 4 layers)
directions: Press into 9 x 13 pan.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine water and sugar and boil 15 minutes and let cool.
Add all other ingredients except ginger ale.
Mix thoroughly and freeze.
Take out of freezer 3 hours before serving time.
No extra ice is needed!
Add by pouring over frozen ingredients, the cold ginger ale.
This recipe totally eliminates a watery tasteless flavored punch.
It is very good and serves 50.

title: microwave rice
directions: Use a 2-quart microwave dish with a cover.
Bring water, butter and salt to a boil on highest setting.
Add rice, stir, and cook on High for 5 minutes.
Then microwave on defrost setting for 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing cover.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in small muffin pan. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a greased/buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, place pieces of cubed bread.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on next.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: In large skillet (or electric skillet), brown meat; drain off fat.
Add onion, soup, green chilies, sauce and milk.
Simmer on medium for 20 minutes.
Fill tortillas with cheese and secure with toothpick.
Sink into meat and sauce mixture and spoon sauce on top.
Simmer on low for 10 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and olives.

title: new england clam chowder(microwave)
directions: In 3-quart microproof casserole, cook bacon on High for 3 minutes.
Stir in onion and potatoes.
Cook, covered, on Saute for 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
In 2-cup glass measure, melt butter on High for 1 minute.
Stir in flour, then add to reserved clam juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Stir liquid, clams, milk, salt and pepper into casserole.
Cook, covered, on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until hot.
Stir once during cooking. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry pineapple treat
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mix in cranberry sauce. Then add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in nuts and pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Put in mold.

title: party punch
directions: Combine frozen lemonade and orange juice diluted with 3 cans water (add sugar to taste).
Add pineapple juice.
Pour into gallon milk jugs.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Just before serving, add 1 quart ginger ale in punch that has been poured into punch bowl.
Float ice in punch bowl.

title: grandma's hot rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over 1/4 cup sugar, salt and shortening and allow to cool (very large bowl).
Mix yeast, 1/2 tablespoon sugar and warm water.
Add to first combination.
Add eggs beaten unto a sponge.
Add 2 cups of the flour and mix thoroughly.
Add remaining 2 cups of flour and beat until dough blisters.
Let rise (covered) in the bowl 2 to 3 hours.
Push dough down, cover and refrigerate. When ready to use, pinch out rolls and place in greased oblong pan. Let rise 2 to 2 1/2 hours and bake in 400° oven about 15 minutes until done.

title: pizza
