directions: Get out as many English muffins as you want.
Spread pizza sauce on them, then sprinkle cheese on them.
Heat the oven to 450°.
Put them in the oven for about 3 minutes.

title: wiener wrap hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut each wiener on a slant into 3 pieces.
Wrap with bacon pieces (1/3 slice) and place toothpick in each piece to hold bacon together.
Place in crock-pot, layering with brown sugar.
Put remaining sugar on top.
Cook 4 hours on high or 8 hours on low.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla mixing well.
Stir in zucchini.
Set mixture aside.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon in a mixing bowl.
Add zucchini mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir until moist.
Grease and fill tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sausage with a little breadcrumbs. Roll out on floured board and divide into 6 squares.
Making sure the eggs are dry, wrap sausage around the eggs.
Coat each egg with egg and breadcrumbs.
Place on oven rack so that fat will drip through and cook 15 to 20 minutes until sausage is thoroughly cooked.
When cool, cut each egg in half lengthwise and decorate with parsley.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; beat in sugar, lemon juice, rind and salt.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until mixture coats a spoon.
Soften gelatin in milk; dissolve in hot custard mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually beat in sugar until meringue stands in still, straight peaks.
Gradually fold custard mixture into egg whites.
Spoon into sherbet glasses and garnish with grated lemon rind.
Chill. Serves 8.

title: schrafft's butterscotch sauce
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients until it reaches a heavy syrup consistency.
Cool and add the vanilla and cream.
If consistency is too heavy, add a little more cream.
This may be served either hot or cold.

title: succotash
directions: Heat the corn and lima beans in butter and a little cream in a saucepan.
Season to taste.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in butter for 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling until cubes are dissolved.
Gradually add noodles and salt until mixture boils.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and garlic, cook 4 minutes.
Add milk, cheese and pepper and continue cooking until cheese melts, stirring constantly.

title: marbled cream cheese brownies
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter together.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla; beat until smooth and set aside.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Makes 3 pies.

title: lazy cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and place in greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onions. Stir in raw rice.
Pour on top of cabbage. Mix soup with 1/2 cup water. Pour on top. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cocoa cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix the sugar, flour, eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla together.
Bring the oleo, Coke, shortening and cocoa to a boil.
Remove from stove and add marshmallows.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in oblong cake pan, greased and floured.

title: banana spice cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla well.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and allspice; add to mixture.
Add bananas and carrots; mix well.
Turn into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, and beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in uncooked pie shell (9 inch).
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300 degrees and bake for 30 minutes.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in greased dish.
Combine other ingredients and mix together to consistency of fine crumbs.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: potato-rutabaga whip
directions: Combine rutabaga, potato and chopped onion in boiling salted water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Mash with light cream and butter until fluffy.
Season to taste.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oven-fried rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a baking dish and top with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: cranberry animals
directions: Chill canned jellied cranberry sauce.
Cut into thin slices. Use cookie cutters to cut into animal shapes to please children.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: Place pineapple and sugar in saucepan and boil for 3 minutes.
Add lemon Jello.
Stir well and cool. Place cream cheese in medium mixing bowl.
Gradually blend in pineapple mixture. Fold in apples, nuts, celery, and Cool Whip.
Place in oblong 9 x 13 inch baking dish and refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine corn, potato, onion, water, bouillon granules and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until corn and potatoes are just tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of milk and the margarine or butter.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onions, parsley, cube and seasoning and mix well.
Simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Gradually add milk and flour and cook until thickened.
Add cheese cubes and stir until melted.

title: layered 24-hour pea salad
directions: Put shredded lettuce in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add water chestnuts, frozen peas, onion, celery, salad dressing and Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.
Chill for 24 hours.
Just before serving, garnish with boiled eggs and bacon bits.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Put nuts in pan.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Roll in mixture of white sugar and cinnamon.
Put in pan on top of nuts.
Boil brown sugar, butter and water until fluffy (about 3 minutes).
Pour over biscuits and bake at 375° about 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: stuffed potatoes parmesan
directions: Cut a slice off the top of each baked potato and scoop out the pulp into a large bowl. Add egg, milk, onion, salt and pepper. Beat well. Spoon mixture back into potato shells. Sprinkle tops with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: bucket of bran muffins
directions: Mix boiling water and shortening and let stand. Add remaining ingredients and stir all together. Can add raisins, nuts, dates, currants, etc. Bake in muffin pans lined with baking cups in a 400° oven for 20 minutes. Mixture will keep for 6 weeks in the refrigerator in a covered container. Makes 4 to 6 dozen muffins.

title: macaroni seafood salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and chill.
Combine remaining ingredients. If fresh shrimp are used, boil 15 minutes, then blanch in cold water and remove shells and center black line.

title: hot pecan spread
directions: Mix all these together and spread in a small casserole dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm with crackers.

title: heart-healthy pumpkin muffins(sugar-free; fat-free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Use dry milk only (do not reconstitute with water). Mix all ingredients together well. Coat muffin tins with cooking spray; fill each muffin cup about half full. Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Makes 24 muffins (regular size) or many more using smaller muffin-size tins. Makes 24 large or 35 or more smaller. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix together sausage and grated cheese.
Add Bisquick and mix well.
Form into balls and bake 7 to 10 minutes at 325°.
Makes 30 to 40 balls.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Mix in blender.
Top with whipped cream.

title: easy blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour and ice cream in bowl; mix well.
Fold in blueberries gently.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with raw vegetables.

title: stain glass cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and oleo.
Let cool.
Add colored marshmallows and nuts and mix well.
Shape into a log and roll in coconut.
Refrigerate overnight and then slice into cookies.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a bag.
Add chicken pieces and shake to coat well.
Heat oil in skillet; add chicken and brown.

Meanwhile, in saucepan, combine pineapple juice from canned pineapple plus enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid, sugar, vinegar, ginger, cornstarch, soy sauce and bouillon cube. Bring to boil and boil until all ingredients are dissolved.
Place browned chicken in large flat baking dish and pour sauce over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add vegetables and pineapple to meat.
Return to oven for an additional 30 minutes.

title: pineapple-buttermilk salad
directions: Combine undrained pineapple and sugar in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add jello, stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and stir until combined.
Fold in whipped topping and pecans.
Spoon into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish and chill until firm.

title: eggs golden rod
directions: Blend soup with milk.
Slice hard-cooked eggs.
Heat and pour over hot buttered toast.

title: dutch stew
directions: Cut beef into
inch
cubes.
Add
cold	water to cover. Cook in bean pot
or earthen dish all day.
Stir occasionally. More water may be needed.
One-half hour before serving, add 1 can peas, drained.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs beating one at a time.
Add alternately syrup and flour.
Begin and end with flour.
Add flavorings.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2 pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: harvest dream cake(spice)
directions: Cream together shortening, milk, vanilla, brown sugar and eggs.
Measure flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice into sifter.
Sift dry ingredients into creamed mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Then mix flour, milk, butter and a sprinkle of pepper.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt oleo.
Sprinkle flour and pecans over oleo.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Spread on crust.
Mix vanilla and chocolate pudding with milk and vanilla.
Blend until thick.
Spread on cheese.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding. Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate overnight or in freezer for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: seafoam
directions: Mix sugar and salt in water. Cook without stirring to 255° or the hard ball stage. Remove from heat and slowly pour over beaten egg whites, beating constantly. Add vanilla.
Continue beating until candy cools and will hold its shape.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Blend cottage cheese and pudding mix.
Fold in Cool Whip. Drain most of the juice from the fruit cocktail.
Blend with the cottage cheese mixture.
Add marshmallows.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: In mixing bowl, combine egg, broccoli, corn, salt and pepper. In small saucepan, melt butter.
Add stuffing mix, tossing to coat.
Stir 3/4 cup of stuffing into vegetable mixture.
Turn into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup of stuffing mix.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Chop cherries and pineapple.
Mix in order given and bake 30 minutes at 250°.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.

title: wisconsin fudge
directions: In a large sauce pan over medium heat, melt butter and cheese, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Sift together sugar and cocoa; add to cheese, mixing well.
Stir in non-fat dry milk, vanilla, and nuts.
Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Chill till firm.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift together the meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Add egg, milk and shortening; beat until smooth. Bake in greased 8-inch square baking pan in a hot oven (425°) for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: "dirt" dessert
directions: Whip pudding with milk, then add Cool Whip.
Mix oleo, cream cheese and sugar in a separate bowl.
Mix all ingredients together.
Crush Oreo cookies very fine.
Alternately layer in bowl Oreo, pudding, Oreo, ending with Oreo.
Add a few gummy worms.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In a big mixing bowl or large pan, mix powdered milk, sugar and Crisco.
Add hot water.
Stir and let cool.
Mix yeast with 1/4 cup of warm water and set aside.
Add eggs and yeast to mix. Add 6 cups flour and mix until dough is smooth.
Cover dough with wax paper and a plate or lid; set overnight.
Take dough out of bowl.
Work on floured board or wrap.
Cut it with cutter. Grease each roll on top with butter and fold.
Put in greased pan and let set for 1 hour.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Spread melted butter on rolls.

title: fruit-salad cake(very special)
directions: Mix all
ingredients well with wooden spoon.
Pour into large, oiled pan.	Sprinkle with 2 cups brown sugar and 2 cups chopped nuts.
Bake 50 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Remove from oven and soak with the following, while both the cake and liquid are hot:
1/2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 pound butter.
Cook until butter and sugar are melted and boiled for 1 minute.

title: breakfast shake
directions: Break banana into small pieces; put in the blender.
Add all the other ingredients.
Secure lid; blend until smooth.
Divide into 2 serving glasses; serve immediately.

title: sausage meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients with hand.
Cook for an hour at 350°.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, water, vanilla and egg.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Nuts and chips are optional.
Bakes at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions in large bowl. Refrigerate until partially set.
Chop nuts.
Wash cranberries and chop in food processor.
Put in a bowl.
Cut oranges in quarters and chop in food processor (include rind).
Blend everything together with the sugar and crushed pineapple and mix with the partially set Jell-O.
Chill thoroughly.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° until firm.

title: unbelievable quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
With 1 tablespoon mixture. shape into balls.
Bake at 350° until done.
Take from oven; push Hershey's Kiss into center and let cool.

title: braised short ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat olive oil in Dutch oven or casserole and brown ribs well on all sides, a few at a time. Drain on paper towel.
Return ribs to Dutch oven or casserole with garlic, celery, carrots, onions and tomatoes.
In a bowl, mix vinegar, wine, tomato paste, sugar, salt, pepper and cayenne. Pour over meat and add stock to cover. Cover, set over medium fire and bring to boil.
Then bake in oven 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 1 hour longer or until meat is tender (adding more broth if needed).
Serves 6.

title: mom's applesauce cake
directions: Measure buttermilk and soda together; let stand until you have mixed other ingredients.
Cream oleo and sugar together.
Add buttermilk and soda mixture and flour.
Add applesauce, salt, allspice, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until top cracks.
Glaze with powdered sugar icing.

title: potato deluxe
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, margarine, cheese and salt.
Add onions and potatoes and mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: frosted raisin bars
directions: Mix sugar, butter or margarine and vanilla.
Add enough milk to make spreading consistency.
Cut in squares.
Makes 20.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Gently mix carrots, pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Combine mayonnaise, honey and lemon juice; pour over first mixture.
Mix. Refrigerate 1 or 2 hours to chill and blend flavors.

title: mom's cherry cream pie
directions: Mix vanilla, sugar and cream cheese.
Fold into whipped cream. Spread into crust.
Spread pie filling on top.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Heat to 375°.
In large bowl, beat shortening and peanut butter until well blended.
Add sugars; beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to other mixture, beating together until well blended.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately place 3 mini kisses on top, pressing down slightly.

title: chicken with 40 cloves of garlic
directions: Rinse chicken in cold water and pat dry.
Put the oil into a heavy casserole with celery, parsley and tarragon.
Add chicken pieces and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Turn chicken several times so all surfaces are coated with oil.
Toss in the 40 peeled garlic cloves; sprinkle with remaining salt and put lid on casserole.
Make a heavy, thick flour and water paste and with your hands, press it all around the rim where the lid and casserole meet, making an even, tight seal.
Cover the lid and the circle of paste with a layer of foil.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not remove lid or foil during baking period. At serving time, remove foil and flour seal.
Serve the chicken with hot toast or thin slices of pumpernickel and spread the soft, buttery garlic cloves on top.

title: rose petal rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir in sugar.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Grease muffin tin and spoon each about 1/2 full of batter.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 10 minutes or until done.
No need to let rise before baking.
Batter may be kept in the refrigerator and used as needed for several days.

title: bread dressing
directions: Moisten bread cubes with milk or hot water.
Add salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and egg.
Melt butter. Simmer chopped onions slightly and add to dressing; mix well.
Allow 1 cup of stuffing to each pound of fowl or game.

title: squash supreme
directions: Melt margarine and toss with dressing mix.
Cook squash in a small amount of water; add soup, sour cream and vegetables.
Layer dressing and squash, ending with dressing.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp appetizer platter
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise; spread over 12-inch pizza pan.
Scatter shrimp on cheese layer, cover with seafood sauce, then layer on cheese, green pepper, onions and tomato.
Cover and chill until serving time.
(Don't make too far ahead.)
Serve with crackers.

title: easy lasagna
directions: In large bowl, mix first 7 ingredients until well blended; set aside.
In skillet, combine browned, drained ground beef and spaghetti sauce.
In 9 x 13-inch dish, spread 3/4 cup of meat sauce over bottom.
Layer 3 uncooked noodles.
Spread half of cheese mixture and 1 1/2 cups of meat sauce over noodles.
Layer 3 more noodles.
Spread rest of cheese mixture.
Layer last 3 noodles.
Spread rest of meat sauce.
Pour water around edges. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; add 2 cups Mozzarella over top and bake for 15 more minutes uncovered.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: Mix together: soups, water and rice.
Put in casserole.
Place cut-up chicken on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered.

title: pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream oleo.
Add vanilla and sugar. Gradually add 2 eggs and 1 cup flour at a time.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Line bottom of pan with chopped nuts, if desired. Bake for 75 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: white wine lobster and pasta
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, melt butter; add shallots and garlic.
Cook 2 minutes; do not brown.
Add tomatoes and chicken broth; cook 8 minutes or until tomatoes are sauce-like, stirring occasionally.
Add whipping cream and wine; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium and cook 3 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Add lobster, mushrooms, dill, salt and lemon rind.
Cook 1 minute or until heated through.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine dates and soda in hot water; let stand.
Cream together white sugar and shortening.
Mix in eggs, cocoa, flour, salt and vanilla.
Add date mixture and half bag of chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top with remaining half bag of chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: grandma joy's angel food delight
directions: Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Slice bananas into small pieces. Place on outer edge of top of cake.
Drain fruit cocktail and place between bananas and hole of cake.
Keep chilled.

title: kielbasa pan roast
directions: In large
skillet over low heat, cook vegetables in oil with seasonings	for about 5 minutes, tossing frequently.
Add kielbasa slices
and
water.
Cover	and
cook over medium low heat, 15
to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender, tossing occasionally.

title: puff pastry
directions: Mix and chill for 8 hours.

title: brioche cheese bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large warm bowl.
Add sugar, salt, warm milk, butter, 3 eggs and 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough more flour to make a soft dough.
On floured board, knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm, draft-free place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down; cover bowl tightly. Refrigerate 5 hours.

title: quick easy french toast
directions: Mix egg, milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Dip bread in mixture and brown on both sides in hot buttered skillet.

title: tuna puff
directions: Put soup in saucepan.
Add cheese; heat until cheese is melted.
Add egg yolks, bread crumbs and tuna.
Fold in egg whites; pour into a slightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with your favorite salad.

title: southampton ham log
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend in mayonnaise, chutney and ham with a fork.
Shape into log form.
Sprinkle on waxed paper the pecans or peanuts.
Roll log in this nut mixture until well covered.
Wrap in foil and chill until firm.
Garnish with cherries and serve with crackers.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Mix both ingredients until well blended and serve with your favorite fruit.

title: potatoe casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with 1/4 cup melted butter and 2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Wash rice.
Mix together and bake in 350° oven.

title: tutti-frutti cake
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar;
add	egg.
Dissolve	soda in small amount
of	hot
water and add to creamed mixture.	Sift baking powder, flour
and	cocoa
together.
Add
to
mixture alternately with the sour milk.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan or small torte
pan for about 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Mix ham, potatoes and cheese in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Add salt and pepper; stir in soup and milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cream square
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add berries, stirring occasionally, until thawed.
Add pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm!

title: ginger snap cookies
directions: Heat molasses to boiling. Add sugar, shortening, and milk. Mix well. Remove from stove. In a bowl sift together flour, cloves, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and ginger. Mix well. Add to molasses mixture and shape into a mound. Wrap in waxed paper, Chill. Roll on board lightly floured with powdered sugar until dough is almost 1/4 inch thick. Dip cookie cutter in powdered sugar each time you cut a cookie. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet
Bake in 375° oven for about 8 minutes or until delicately browned.

title: honey-nut wheat muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and flour mixture.
Shape into round loaf, wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight.
Slice in thin slices.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and cook until it gets a little syrupy. If not enough sauce, add more vinegar.
When chicken is almost done; split and brush, especially good on leg quarters.

title: quick, easy pretzels(kids can make em!)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt and flour. Knead until smooth, shiny and elastic.
The kids may pound, turn, stretch and punch to their delight for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cut into smaller pieces and roll into ropes, coil, whatever shapes you desire.
Do not let rise.

title: brides pie
directions: Mix together and pour into crust.
Freeze 2 hours.

title: chicken-rotelle soup
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken.
In Dutch oven, brown chicken in melted margarine.
Remove chicken.
Saute onion, celery and carrots until tender.
Add parsley, salt, bay leaves, thyme, 4 cups chicken broth and the chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together remaining ingredients. Spread over cake mixture. Bake about 1 hour.

title: fillet of sole in white wine
directions: Put fillets into greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Mix wine, onion, butter and dry seasonings.
Pour over fish; cover casserole.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt nettie's german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour on top of coconut and pecans.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside. Cream butter; add cheese and nuts. Stir in dry ingredients and form into roll(s). Wrap in wax paper and chill several hours or overnight. Slice thinly and bake about 10 minutes at 350°. Watch closely and do not brown.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Blend the butter, oil, sugars, vanilla and egg.
Sift and stir in the flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake on ungreased sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: date pudding
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix together nuts, dates and sweet milk and add to flour mixture.

title: crookneck squash pickles
directions: Combine squash and onion.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 1 hour.
Combine green pepper, vinegar, sugar, celery and mustard seed.
Add squash and onions; return to a boil.
Pack in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: punch cake
directions: Slice berries.
Add glaze and frozen berries in a bowl.
Mix. Slice cake and put a layer of cake in a large bowl.
Add a layer of strawberry mixture, then a layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat.
Finish with Cool Whip.

title: golden cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower in boiling water for about 20 minutes.
Set aside.
Melt the two tablespoons of butter in a skillet.
Now add the flour and stir until mixture is blended, being sure not to burn or scorch mixture.
Do over a low heat.
If burned, start over. Slowly add milk and stir until thick and even.
Add the salt, pepper, pimientos, onion and pinch of sugar.
Blend this mixture. Put cauliflower in baking dish and pour the sauce over it. Sprinkle with the bread crumbs and sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: skillet corn and chicken
directions: In skillet in margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove chicken.
Drain most of margarine from skillet.
In skillet, combine rest of the ingredients.
Heat to boiling. Return chicken to skillet.
Cook on low heat until chicken is tender.
Serves 4.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Combine cheeses in medium bowl.
In small bowl, combine taco sauce and eggs until thoroughly blended.
In 9 x 9-inch baking pan, place 1/2 cheese, taco sauce mixture and then remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
To serve, cut into 1-inch squares and place on tortilla chips.
Best served warm.

title: macaroni pizza
directions: Mix together.
Put into baking dish.
Line top with pepperoni. Bake until bubbly (making sure it's juicy), then sprinkle top with Mozzarella cheese.
Put under broiler until cheese melts. Serve with garlic bread.
Bake at 350°.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Boil hard for 3 minutes.
Stir constantly to keep from sticking.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup Baker's semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Beat until chips melt.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat to blend.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill, then cut into squares.

title: sweet chili franks
directions: Combine chili sauce, jelly and 1 juice.
Heat until jelly melts and mixture is heated through.
Slowly stir about 1/4 cup of sauce into cornstarch then blend into hot mixture.
Cook until sauce thickens.
Add franks and heat until glazed, about 10 minutes.
Can also be used with meatballs (browned) or Vienna sausages.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package, then drain.
Melt 3/4 stick of garlic cheese, 3/4 stick of Velveeta cheese, mushroom soup and milk in saucepan or double boiler; stir until mixed well. Add this to the broccoli and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This serves 12.

title: cream sauce
directions: Heat milk in saucepan.
Mix flour and sugar with the cold milk.
Stir into hot milk, stirring until mixture boils and thickens.
Add butter and caraway seed, stirring to melt butter.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Combine all other ingredients and marinate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Add pineapple to cream cheese. Mix pepper, onion and salt. Add 1/2 cup nuts. Form into two balls.
Roll in remaining nuts.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients together; makes a lot, can be frozen or can cut ingredients in half to make smaller portion.
To serve:
Mix 1/4 or 1/3 cup of mix for each cup of hot water.

title: drippy icing
directions: Combine all in a small pan.
Stir all the time while cooking. Boil until thickened.
Ready to use on cake.
Good on chocolate cake.
Can flavor with chocolate, if desired.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into a ball. Roll ball in chopped nuts.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Set aside. Beat together cake mix, 3/4 cup evaporated milk and margarine. Bake half the cake batter in greased 9 x 13 pan in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and spread caramel mixture on top of layer. Add pecans and chocolate chips. Spread with remaining batter and continue baking for 15 to 20 minutes. (You can use any chocolate cake mix
instead of German chocolate, if you wish.)

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: If you don't care for walnuts, can use all pecans.

title: shrimp canapes
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Fold in mayonnaise, cheese, salt and paprika.
Spread on bread and top with shrimp.
(Or shrimp can be mixed in with other ingredients.)
Place on cookie sheet and broil until light brown.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend oil and sugar until creamy; add eggs and vanilla.
Fold in zucchini and dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; grease and flour pans.
Makes 2 regular loaves.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Mix in order by hand.
Do not use a mixer.
Spoon into oiled loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dee-dee's pork chops
directions: Grease skillet; brown chops in skillet.
Place sliced onion over chops.
Simmer, covered, until onions are opaque.
Mix 1 cup of orange juice with 1 cup of water; pour over chops and onion. Simmer, covered, until tender, approximately 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: velvet cake pound cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Add butter and mix until damp. Add milk and beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flavoring and beat until smooth.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 275°.

title: baked potato wedges
directions: Pour Crisco Oil into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Scrub potatoes. Cut lengthwise into quarters.
Blot cut edges with paper towel. Put potatoes in pan.
Turn to coat evenly with oil, leaving potatoes cut sides up in a single layer.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt, pepper and cheese, if used.
Bake at 425 for 30-40 minutes or until fork tender.
Serve plain or with sour cream.
Add extra salt and pepper, if desired.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain. Mix all ingredients together. Heat until cheese melts. Serve over chips or burritos. Can also use as a dip.

title: coconut date balls
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and dates.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add cereal and pecans.
Chill.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: saltine toffee bars
directions: Bring sugar and butter to a boil.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Pour over saltines (single layer, touching).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Pour chocolate morsels over and spread.
Place pan in freezer for 1 hour.
Break into pieces.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat together for 3 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes (9 x 13-inch pan).

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and medium onion.
Mix together.
Mix soup with milk.
Spread meat and onion in casserole dish.
Pour liquid over meat.
Do not stir.
Spread Tater Tots evenly over meat and liquid.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Prepare fruit as directed.
Mix and sift flour, salt and sugar into mixing bowl.
Combine salad oil and milk in measuring cup. Whip with fork.
Pour all at once over flour mixture.
Mix with fork until dampened.
Turn pastry into square cake pan, 8 x 8 x 2. Pat out to cover bottom of pan and push dough up along sides to depth of about 1 inch.
Arrange fruit over pastry.
Sprinkle streusel over fruit.
Bake in hot oven. 425° 40 to 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Measure all ingredients before starting.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Then add all ingredients in order listed.
Cook in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ground beef and noodles casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown hamburger in oil, add soup, garlic salt and salt; mix well.
Add noodles and pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: browned rice
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add rice and brown.
Add consomme.
Put in casserole dish; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Place cucumbers and onions in gallon jar.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to jar.
Put in refrigerator.
Next day, stir a couple of times.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda.
Mix together the water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients to the mayonnaise mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake as loaf cake or in 2 (8-inch) round cake pans.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and marshmallows (broken into small pieces) in boiling water.
Pour in cold water and chill.
Before it gets too firm, add pineapple, pecans, rice and whipped cream.
Stir well. Chill.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Mix together well.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: "kid's" special sandwich
directions: Cut crusts off bread and save to feed the birds.
Spread bread slices lightly with Miracle Whip.
Place bologna between bread slices.
Cut sandwich into 1-inch squares.
Place sandwich pieces on a small plate and serve with potato chips and a sweet midget pickle.
Serve with a glass of milk over ice.
Serve one little child.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 mixture, then mix remaining ingredients together.
Add it and top with the last of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: lemon graham squares
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole crackers.
Heat to boiling the margarine, milk, sugar and egg.
Add coconut, nuts and crumbs.
Spread over crackers in pan.
Chill.
Frost with Lemon Icing.

title: chicken curry
directions: Season chicken breast with garlic salt and salt and pepper. Bake with onion and little water.
Cut up and put in sauce and leave overnight.
Heat slow.
Serve over rice.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix with water.
Dip fish in dry flour first, then in the batter.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breast.
Remove any bone and tear in small pieces.
Place into greased casserole dish.
Mix peppers, onions and pimentos together in skillet with enough water or broth from cooked chicken or margarine and cook until done, about 15 minutes (may add water).
Add mushroom soup and chicken soup to this and boil until well mixed.
Pour this over chicken.
Do not stir.
Mix flour with broth with fork until smooth.
Pour over ingredients. Do not stir.
This makes crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tex-mex lasagna(a vegetarian dish)
directions: In a bowl, stir together the spaghetti sauce, water, beans, corn and chili seasoning.
Spread 1 cup of this mixture over the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Arrange 4 lasagna noodles over the sauce.
Cover with 1 cup of sauce.
Spread half of the Ricotta on top of noodles and sauce.
Top with 4 more lasagna noodles. Spread remaining Ricotta on top of noodles.
Top with remaining noodles and sauce.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
When ready to cook, preheat oven to 350°.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover lasagna and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake an additional 15 minutes, uncovered.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: chicken imperial
directions: Pound chicken breasts to flatten (or have butcher put through their machine).
Combine bread crumbs, cheese and seasonings.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then in crumb mixture; roll chicken, tucking in ends.
Place in baking dish, dot with butter and bake for 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: cashew chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken (microwave 4 minutes on High, then rotate and cook another 4 minutes, or bake until done).
Dice chicken.
Mix chicken, dill weed, mayonnaise, mustard and lemon juice.
Place on top of bed of lettuce.
Sprinkle cashews on top.
Serve with Paul Newman's oil and vinegar dressing.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, peas, onion, eggs, cheese, bacon bits, and spread mayonnaise over it.Then layer again. May add a little cheese and bacon to garnish top layer of mayonnaise.
Chill all day or over night. Be sure to use Hellman's as this enhances the taste.

title: monkey cake
directions: Mix 2/3 cup sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Shake pieces in bag.
Place first 2 cans of cut biscuits in bottom of greased tube pan.
Cut second can of biscuits and shake in bag.
Set aside.
Combine sugar (1 cup) and butter in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Drizzle on first layer.
Top.
Add raisins and nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn out of pan while warm.
Pull apart and enjoy.

title: shell salad
directions: Mix together; let marinate overnight.

title: wild rose jelly
directions: Place wild rose petals in a pot with cold water.
Bring to boil and boil for
minutes.
Strain the mixture and add 1/4 cup of strained strawberry	juice and enough water to make 2 quarts in all.
Then add
sugar
and stir and bring to boil. Pour in	fruit
pectin,	stirring while pouring.
Boil for 1/2 minute. Pack in sterilized jars and put in fruit closet after cooling.

title: peggy's special chicken bake
directions: Pour dry rice into bottom of baking dish.
Arrange breasts on top.
Pour spice mix from Rice-A-Roni on top of breasts.
Spoon soup on top of all; pour 1 can water into dish.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add boiling water and lemon juice.
Cook until thick.
Stir in egg yolks, cook 1 minute longer.
Add butter. Cool.
Pour in baked pie shell and top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: no bake holiday orange balls
directions: Mix together wafer crumbs, coconut and sugar.
Add orange concentrate and mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Store in covered container overnight.
Makes between 3 to 4 dozen.

title: maple nut cookies
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and egg.
Add vanilla, maple syrup, maple extract and mix well.
Mix flour and baking powder and mix well in batter.
Add nuts and drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: elephant stew supreme
directions: Cut elephant into bite size chunks.
This should take about 6 months.
Cook over bonfire about 6 weeks.

Add potatoes, onions, carrots, salt and pepper. Stew the tomatoes, then add those. Serves about 5,000, but if more are expected, add the rabbits but only if necessary since most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: green jello salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and keep cool until used.

title: easy quiche
directions: Mix first 6
ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 375 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peachy delight
directions: Mix all ingredients for first layer and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in washed strawberries and water.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in food coloring. Chill 30 minutes or until mixture is slightly warm.
Fold in remaining berries.
Pile into pie shell.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
In small mixing bowl whip the cream until soft peaks form.
Sprinkle pudding over cream and beat until stiff.
Pipe around edge of pie or dollop on individual slices.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash 1/2 cup beans until smooth.
Stir in sugar, coconut and margarine.
Blend in eggs, stir in other 1/2 cup beans and pour into pie shell.
Bake 35 minutes at 325° or until done.
Can use walnuts or pecans instead of beans.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender.
Drain and chill. Add remaining ingredients and toss well.
Let stand in refrigerator to chill.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Heat raisins and water slowly to swell raisins 10 to 12 minutes.
Add sugar and lemon juice or vinegar and salt.
Boil very slowly until thickened.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar and melted butter together.
Add bread cubes; mix well.
Add pineapple with juice to the bread mixture; mix well.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and bake for 45 minutes.
May be doubled.

title: turkey frame soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large stew pot and bring to a boil, then simmer for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place fruit in bottom of baking dish.
Cream together butter and 3/4 cup sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Spoon this over fruit.
Sift together 1 cup sugar and cornstarch and sprinkle over dough on fruit.
Pour boiling water on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: strawberry glaze whipped cream pie
directions: Simmer 1 cup of fresh strawberries in 2/3 cup of water for 3 minutes.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Add 1/3 cup water.
Mix until smooth.
Add to strawberry mixture.
Boil, stirring until clear and thick.
Add red food coloring.
Cool.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Place blueberries in dish.
Top with melted margarine. Combine sugar, milk, flour and vanilla in dish.
Pour over blueberries and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together. Batter will be thick. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
In a separate bowl combine shortening, salt and sugar.
Add the boiling water and stir until shortening is melted.
When mixture is lukewarm add yeast and beaten eggs.
Blend in sifted flour until well blended; place in greased bowl.
Cover and set in refrigerator for 2 to 12 hours. Shape into balls and place on baking sheet or in muffin tins. Brush tops with butter.
Let raise to double in bulk.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes and slice in half.
Put in baking dish, cut side up.
Top each with a pat of butter and salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies, reserving 1/2 cup. Cut in butter in remaining cookie mix.
Layer cookies in bottom of oblong pan.
Mix 2 cups Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Layer on top of cookies.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Layer on top of Cool Whip mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and cookie crumbs. Refrigerate for about 2 hours before serving.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Heat milk to scalding. Pour over bread crumbs. Cool and add sugar, butter, eggs, salt, raisins and cinnamon or nutmeg. Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake until silver knife inserted in pudding comes out clean. Serve warm, with or without hard sauce or cream. Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad in a sauce
directions: Drain all fruits and mix in large bowl.
Cook mixed fruit juices with 2 to 3 tablespoons cornstarch in microwave until thickened and clear.
Cool.
Stir into fruit.
Fold in bananas. Yields 6 to 8 quarts (fills punch bowl).
Serves 100 depending on how many other salads are served.

title: bran muffins
directions: Before creaming the above,
pour
water
over the 1 cup 100% bran allowing
to cool slightly.
Cream Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt and buttermilk.
Blend
into
batter
the 100% bran.
Add apricots and 2 cups
bran flakes.
Mix thoroughly.
This can be refrigerated in 1/2
gallon
container.
Cover and never stir or mix again.
Dip as you
want
to
bake
and
put in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 or 20 minutes or if you want to you can bake all and freeze in bags.
This will keep in refrigerator for 5 weeks.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots 10 minutes; drain.
Mix rest of vegetables; cook 5 minutes.
Mix the rest of the ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until casserole is set.
Serves 4.

title: one step tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Combine remaining ingredients and add meat.
Mix well.
Pour in glass cake pan and bake at 305° for 45 minutes.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Pour whiskey over raisins, pineapple and cherries.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix spices with flour. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add fruit mixture and pecans. Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Cookies not only keep well but improve after 2 or 3 days. Yield:
6 dozen cookies.

title: rotel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Ro-Tel; place in microwave until melted.
Then add Ro-Tel; mix well.

title: quickee tuna casserole
directions: Blend milk and soup.
Add rest of ingredients in a 1-quart casserole.
Microwave for 7 to 8 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chow chow relish
directions: Wash and drain vegetables.
Peel onions; remove seeds from peppers.
Chop and measure all vegetables.
Dissolve salt in 8 cups of water; pour over vegetables.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain; if too salty, rinse and drain vegetables again.
Mix vegetables with sugar, mustard seed and vinegar.
Simmer 20 minutes; then bring to boiling.
Pack boiling hot into hot jars; seal at once.
Makes about 4 pints.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna, noodles, soup and peas together.
Place in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with crushed potato chips; bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain. Brown sausage.
Drain.
Melt cheese in double boiler.
Put hamburger meat, sausage and cheese in crock-pot.
Stir in tomatoes.
Put the crock-pot on low and serve with tortilla chips.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Chop eggplant into 1-inch disks and then quarter.
Boil until soft, approximately 20 minutes.
Drain.
Mash eggplant with tomatoes.
Add onions and green pepper.
Add stuffing and egg. Add seasonings.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish with butter. Pour mixture into casserole.
Press in.
Add milk to cover.
Top with grated cheese (can be mixed into eggplant mixture, also).
Cook at 350° until bubbly, approximately 1 hour.

title: popular green bean casserole
directions: Defrost beans by placing packages in single layer in microwave oven.
Microwave at Low 10 to 12 minutes, turning over and rearranging packages every 2 to 3 minutes.
Separate beans into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix with canned soup, milk and pimentos to blend well.
Cook to 170°, covered with plastic wrap loosely to vent.
When oven reaches 170°, arrange topping of French fried onions in a ring around the edge of dish; toss to mix, if desired. Makes about 8 servings.

title: hawaiian cake(super bowl bake off '94 - 2nd place)
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Let it cool.
Cook pineapple in water and sugar; bring to boil.
Use fork to make holes.
Pour pineapple mixture on cake.
Let cool.
Mix pudding as directed and put on top of cake.
When set, put whipped cream on top of pudding; garnish with cherries and roasted pecans.
Anonymous author.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together; put in baking dish.

title: onion dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Beat cream cheese, sour cream and onion juice until smooth.
Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: trilby
directions: Mix all.
Refrigerate at least twelve hours.
Unmold on serving plate.
Serve with crackers.
Garnish with parsley.

title: delicious chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, onions and mayonnaise; set aside.
Mix 2 beaten eggs, butter, chicken broth and stuffing; set aside.
Mix remaining 2 beaten eggs and milk; set aside.

title: german pizza
directions: Put oil in pan (use electric frying pan).
Spread half the potatoes evenly on the bottom.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with layer of half the onions and green peppers.
Layer with 1/2 the meat.
Repeat layers.
Cover and cook over low heat until potatoes are tender.
Beat eggs and spread over evenly.
Cover and cook until eggs are set.
Top with cheese.
Cover until melted. Sprinkle with parsley (optional).

title: tallarini
directions: Saute ground beef in butter.
Mix together all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cable car tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 2-quart casserole, gently toss noodles, tuna, celery, pepper and water chestnuts.
In a saucepan, combine celery soup and milk.
Heat, stirring until smooth.
Add onions, mayonnaise, thyme, salt and only 1/2 cup of the cheese. Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add sauce to casserole; mix gently and thoroughly.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese and almonds.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly and lightly browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice ambrosia
directions: Combine as given; fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate awhile before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except broccoli and mix well.
Mix in broccoli.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple delight salad
directions: Dissolve jellos in hot water.
Add and stir in cottage cheese, pineapple, mayonnaise, lemon juice and horseradish mustard.
Pour into mold and chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Melt butter and coat chicken. Break chips into tiny pieces. Cover chicken with chips. Cook at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Butter or spray crock-pot. Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pot and top with cheese and paprika. Cook 3 1/2 hours on low.

title: sapa
directions: My mother always made this when we were sick.
It is an old recipe.

title: cinnamon date slices
directions: Combine flour, walnuts, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking powder.
Beat butter, 2/3 cup sugar and zest until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Beat in flour mixture. Divide in half. Wrap and chill.
Simmer dates, 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 cup water until dates soften, about 10 minutes. Cool.
Heat oven to 325°. Roll each piece of dough between sheets of floured, waxed paper to a 12 x 6-inch rectangle.
Spread dates lengthwise down the center. Lift dough over filling.
Seal seam.
Put on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until golden, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Dust with confectioners sugar. Slice.
Makes about 24 cookies.

title: spinach cheddar bake
directions: In a bowl, combine spinach, crackers, egg, onion and salt. Stir in 1/2 of cheese.
Put into greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve sugar and jello in cranberries; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
When the mixture becomes slightly congealed, stir in 2 cups finely diced celery and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Refrigerate until jelled.

title: chicken a-la-can-can
directions: Combine soups, water & chicken, add Minute rice right from box. Mix and bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat about 10 minutes. Or: bake in oven 1/2 hour. An optional garnish is parsley. Top with onion rings.

title: peas n' dumplings
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; mixture will be pasty.
Boil about 4 to 5 cups water.
Drop mixture, using a teaspoon, into the boiling water.
I usually use 1/2 teaspoon of mixture on a teaspoon, it makes a nice size dumpling.
When dumpling mixture is all used up, add frozen peas.
Cook until peas are done.
Drain water; salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in flour gradually, beating well.
Mix in vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Slowly stir in 7-Up.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding together.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well and refrigerate.

title: milky way cake
directions: Chop candy bars; combine with 1 stick of margarine in top of double boiler.
Heat over hot water until melted, then set aside. Cream sugar with remaining stick of margarine, add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Combine flour and salt.
Stir soda into buttermilk; add alternately with flour, beating smooth after each addition.
Stir in nuts, vanilla and melted candy-margarine mixture; pour into lightly greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: truite a la creame zugoise(trout in herbed cream sauce)
directions: In a heavy 12-inch skillet, melt the butter over moderate heat. When the foam begins to subside, add the shallots or scallions and stirring frequently, cook for about 5 minutes or until they are soft and transparent, but not brown.
Watch carefully for any sign of burning and regulate the heat accordingly.
Stir in the parsley, chervil, thyme and tarragon, then pour in the wine and mix well. Remove the skillet from the heat.
Pat the trout fillets completely dry with paper towels and sprinkle them on both sides with the salt and pepper.
Arrange them on top of the herbs in the skillet in one layer, overlapping them slightly if necessary.
Cut a circle of foil as large or a bit larger than the skillet and press it gently, but firmly over the fish.
Return the skillet to moderate heat and simmer the trout for about 5 minutes or until the flesh flakes easily when prodded gently with a fork.
With a slotted spatula, transfer the fillets to a heated platter and drape fresh foil over it to keep the fish warm while you prepare the sauce.
Stirring constantly, bring the liquid remaining in the skillet to a boil until it is reduced to a thin film that barely covers the bottom of the pan.

Reduce the heat to moderate and still stirring, pour in the cream and any liquid that has accumulated around the fish. Continue to boil the sauce, stirring occasionally, until it is thick enough to coat the whisk heavily.
This may take from 5 to 10 minutes.
Taste for seasoning, then pour the sauce over the trout, covering them completely.
Serve at once.

title: quick cheese cakes
directions: Cream together.
Line cupcake liners with a vanilla wafer. Pour creamed mixture over enough to cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: granny's red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
In separate bowl, cream oil and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add food color.
Mix well until blended. Combine buttermilk and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add to oil-sugar mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and vanilla. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 layers.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix all together and pour half of butter into mix.
Mix together well and pour into pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: athenaeum rolls
directions: Add shortening to scalded milk.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to milk mixture.
Add eggs, salt, flour and 1/2 cup sugar to yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Allow to rise until double in bulk, about 2 hours.
Shape into cloverleaf or desired shape, using melted butter in forming rolls.
Let rise until double in bulk about 45 minutes to an hour.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in shallow baking dish.
Make 5 cuts 2/3 through loaf on Spam.
Place in baking dish.
Drain fruit; save juice.
Combine cornstarch and brown sugar.
Stir into juice and add margarine.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in fruit and simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon over split loaf and sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush Oreos fine with spoon or blender.
Melt butter and mix with cookies.
Mash them into bottom of large container.
Put ice cream over cookies.
Spread chocolate syrup over ice cream and Cool Whip over chocolate syrup.
Sprinkle pecans over Cool Whip and arrange cherries on top.
Freeze overnight.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, pepper and onions.
Drain well.
Mix ketchup, mustard, vinegar, brown sugar and salt.
Then add beans and hamburger mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or cook on high in slow cooker for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheddar apple pizza
directions: Roll pastry to fit a greased 12-inch pizza pan. Flute edges. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Arrange apples in single layer. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine the brown sugar, walnuts, cinnamon and nutmeg. Sprinkle over cheese. Cut butter into small pieces and dot top of pizza. Bake for 20 minutes or until apples are tender. Cut into wedges. Serve warm. Yield: 12 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix with milk in saucepan.
Add peanut butter.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Cool cooked pudding 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill 3 hours.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix the ingredients with a mixer until smooth.
Then mix by hand 2 cups chocolate chips (regular milk chocolate) and 2 cups chopped pecans into mixture.
Pour into a Bundt pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.
You can tell when it's done by touching top to see if it's firm.
Slice with a sharp knife.

title: cake frosting and decorating
directions: Beat Crisco and 2 cups powdered sugar on low until creamy. Add egg white, salt and remaining powdered sugar. Mix until all is moistened.

title: gourmet hot dogs
directions: Mix everything in electric frypan and simmer at 220° for 1 hour.
(Can be frozen once made.)

title: company casserole
directions: Set cooked noodles aside.
Saute ground chuck in oil.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt, tomato sauce, tomato paste and 1 cup water.
Cook 1/2 hour, then remove from heat.
Combine in a separate bowl the cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream.

title: jello pudding cake
directions: Mix white cake mix as directed on box. Bake. After cake has baked, poke holes in it with a fork.
Dissolve the Jell-O in the hot water and then add the cold water.
Pour over cake. Chill awhile.
Make vanilla pudding as directed on box. Spread over cake. Spread whipped topping over that.

title: tennie's fig cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Cream
margarine
and
sugar
until light and fluffy; add eggs, 1 at
a
time.
Beat
well.
Add
vanilla.
Sift
flour, cinnamon, allspice, salt and soda.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with buttermilk, saving a small amount of flour mixture to dredge pecans
in.
Cut up the fig preserves and add to the mixture.
Add pecans.
Bake at 325° in a prepared tube pan for 1 hour, then at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas (casserole)
directions: Saute onions in butter; combine with soup, broth and green chilies and beat well.

title: squash cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly sugar, Crisco, eggs, squash and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter in a saucepan. Combine sugar and cereal; pour over peanut butter. Blend mixture with hands and form into 1/2 inch balls; let cool. Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips in a double pan; pour over balls.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and whole orange.
Dissolve jello in 3 cups hot water.
Add sugar and rest of ingredients.
Chill.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in olive oil with onion, garlic and parsley.
Add tomato paste, water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon to remember and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix eggs, Ricotta or cottage cheese and grated Mozzarella cheese.
Arrange lasagna in baking dish in layers, alternating with layers of sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Ricotta until lasagna is all used.
Sprinkle with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in moderate oven at 375°
for about 20 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Roll out dough and spread peanut butter on it.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Chill and slice.

title: banana cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil lightly and dust and flour 2 round layer pans.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in 1/3 cup sugar; continue until very stiff and glossy.
Sift remaining sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and soda into another bowl.
Add oil, mashed bananas, half of buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute on medium speed on mixer.
Add remaining buttermilk and egg yolks. Beat 1 minutes; fold in egg whites.
Fold nuts in gently.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Eat frosted or plain.

title: puppy chow
directions: Over low heat, melt chocolate, peanut butter and margarine in saucepan.
Put cereal in large bowl.
Pour melted mixture over cereal in large bowl.
Put confectioners sugar in large brown paper bag.
Add cereal mixture.
Shake until coated.
Put in airtight container and refrigerate.

title: english toffee
directions: Put margarine, sugars and butter in an electric fry pan at about 400 degrees, stirring constantly.
When at a free boil, boil for 9 minutes.
Pour onto a buttered cookie sheet already covered with 1/2 cup finely chopped walnuts.
Finely chop 1-1/2 8-oz. bars of milk chocolate and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.
When set, break into pieces.
Recipe is easy -- timing critical.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients with hash browns.
Top with 2 cups cornflakes, crushed, and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: german chocolate frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks and butter in heavy saucepan; bring to a boil and cook over medium heat for 12 minutes, stirring constantly. Add vanilla, coconut and pecans; stir until frosting is cool and of spreading consistency. Spread between layers and on top and sides of German chocolate cake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In saucepan, bring to boil the butter, onion and water.
Add broccoli; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add the Minute rice; let stand 5 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and cream of celery soup; place in buttered casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pam's chicken souffle
directions: Cut 2 slices of bread into cubes.
Grease a 10 1/2 x 7 x 2-inch casserole or any 1 1/2-quart rectangular shape.
Combine chicken, mayonnaise, celery, parsley, onion and pimento.
Add salt, pepper and Accent.
Spread over bread cubes.
Add other 4 slices that have been cubed over the mixture.
Combine beaten eggs and milk.
Pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
One 1 hour before serving, preheat oven to 325°.
Pour undiluted soup over mixture and bake 50 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 10 more minutes. Serves 6.

title: artoklasia
directions: Dilute yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Add sugar, salt and stir.
Add water and oil.
Add 3 cups flour mixed with cinnamon and stir until batter is smooth.
Add remainder of flour until dough is soft but firm.
Knead until bubbles appear on surface of dough and it is smooth and satiny.

title: cherry sub gum
directions: Cream margarine and flour and add pecans (makes a powdery mess).
Spread over the bottom of casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes or until brown at 450°.
Cool; run fork through it to loosen.
(It will still be powdery.)
In 1 bowl, put Dream Whip and cold milk. Whip until fluffy.
In another bowl, put cream cheese.
Cream with confectioners sugar.
Gradually add cream cheese mixture to Dream Whip using mixer.
Pour over crust-like mixture and cool.
When cooled, pour cherry pie filling over.
Cool, cut into squares and serve.

title: salmon balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into small to medium balls. Place into frying pan and cook.
Rotate balls so they do not burn.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix well.
Bake in unbaked pie crust at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: k.c.'s elks bread(never fails; good for a family)
directions: Put all dry ingredients together and mix.
Add shortening and hot water.
Mix 10 minutes in machine (we have a big commercial mixer) or knead it good.
Raise, punch down, raise again, then put in pans and raise before you put it in oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 50 rolls and 2 loaves of bread or make what you want.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pie shell for 10 minutes; remove from oven and reduce heat to 325°.
In a saucepan over low heat, melt semi-sweet chocolate chips with butter or margarine.
In large mixer bowl, beat chocolate mixture with remaining ingredients, except nuts, until smooth.
Add nuts and pour into pasty shell.
Bake 35-45 minutes or until center is set; cool. Serve warm or at room temperature.
Good with ice cream.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix together over medium low heat.
Serve immediately.

title: fish chowder("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: In about 4-quart agate pot, put fish, salt and water to cover. Bring to boil and simmer until fish flakes easily.
Remove from stock and slice potatoes into fish stock.

title: apple pandowdy dessert
directions: Peel, core and slice the apples.
Place them in a baking dish. Drizzle the molasses or syrup over the apples, then sprinkle with with nuts, sugar, spices and salt.
Slowly pour hot water over the top.
Bake the mixture for 20 minutes at 350°, until the apples are tender.
Squish the biscuit dough into a big ball.
Roll the dough into a crust and spread it over the apples.
Bake the pandowdy about 15 more minutes, until the crust is lightly browned.
Serve it hot or cold with cream.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix cooked beef, onion, seasoning and beans for 10 minutes until done.
Mix salsa and soup; set aside.
Spray square pan with Pam.
Layer meat, corn tortillas, cheese and soup mixture until done.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pesto
directions: Blend basil, garlic and olive oil in blender or food processor until smooth.
Add pine nuts and cheese; blend until smooth.
When ready to use, add more cheese if desired.

title: uncle bill's jerky
directions: Slice deer or beef into strips 1/4-inch thick.
Marinate meat overnight.
Lay strips on oven rack and place in a 140° oven until desired dryness, approximately 6 to 10 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients until well moistened.
Chill for a while before serving.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Cut large flour tortillas in half.
Spread mixture on tortilla and roll up. Place in casserole dish (9 x 13-inch or larger) seam side down. Pour whipping cream on top.
Spread grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Very good!
Feeds 6.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix cornmeal, egg, flour and milk (mixture should be thick enough to stick to wieners, just a little runny).
Dip wieners into mixture and cook in hot grease, deep enough so wieners will float back to top.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed; gradually beat in sugar. Stir in remaining ingredients. Grease cookie sheet. Pour batter on cookie sheet and put chopped pecans on top. Bake for 15 minutes at 375°. Sprinkle a towel that isn't fuzzy (cloth) with powdered sugar and put cake on it. Roll it up and let it cool. Then put filling on the cake and roll it up again in foil.

title: bob's beer-fried onion rings
directions: Combine flour and beer in large bowl; blend thoroughly with wooden spoon.
Cover bowl; keep at room temperature at least 3 hours.
Divide onion rounds into individual rings.
In large skillet, heat enough oil to drop in onion rings.
Dip a few onion rings at a time into prepared batter, then into hot (375°) oil. Fry until golden brown.
Place on cookie sheet lined with paper towels; keep warm in preheated 200°
oven.
Can be frozen and reheated in 400° oven, if desired.
Makes enough for 4 to 6 servings.

title: fudge brownie pie with nut crust
directions: Blend oleo with sugar, flour and nuts.
Press over bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate (not rim).

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Mix flour and salt in a bowl.
Make a well in center and add eggs.
Blend thoroughly.
Turn dough onto a floured board and knead.
Cover and let stand 30 minutes.
Roll until dough is paper thin.
Cut dough into lengthwise strips in desired widths.
Let dry thoroughly.
If not used immediately, store in air tight container in refrigerator.

title: quick cookies
directions: Timing is very important!
Have all ingredients and a clock ready before you start.

title: no-cal soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan.
Cook until vegetables are tender. Eat as much as you like.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Completely soften beans by cooking in boiling water on the stove. Drain the water off of beans and transfer the beans to crock-pot. Add all remaining ingredients to beans and stir to blend entirely. Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours. Top with sour cream and Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: chuck or shoulder roast
directions: Use a
piece
of
aluminum foil that can seal the roast well. Put the roast in the aluminum foil that has been placed in a
pan with
at least 1-inch sides.
Sprinkle the soup mix over the roast.
Put
the soup and water on top of the roast, too.
Cook in a
425° oven for 2 hours.
Be sure you seal the foil well.

title: great northern baked beans
directions: Wash beans.
Put in pot.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until beans are swollen.
Drain water off.
Put beans in a baking pot and add water to cover.
Add molasses, pork, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 6 1/2 to 8 hours in oven.
Check often and add more water, if needed.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Cube Velveeta in a microwavable bowl.
Drain tomatoes and mix with cheese.
Add Hormel chili.
Microwave, stirring frequently, until cheese has melted and all ingredients are blended well. Serve as a dip with tortilla chips.

title: vanilla wafer cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Beat in egg and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° 12-15 min. until edges are
golden brown. Cool on wire rack. Makes 7 dozen.

title: chinese chows
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add remainder.
Spread 1/2-inch thick in pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cut in squares.
Roll in sugar.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together in a large bowl.
Cut shortening into mixture with pastry blender until mixture looks like rice grains.
Add milk and stir with fork.
Put dough on board and knead 6 to 8 times.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
Spread melted butter over dough.
Put sugar and cinnamon on top of butter.
Roll up in a long roll and cut into 12 pieces. Place in muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: breakfast strada
directions: In a 5 x 10-inch greased dish, layer bread, meat, mushrooms and cheese.
Mix Egg Beaters with milk and pour over all. Refrigerate overnight.
(Remove from refrigerator approximately 15 minutes before baking.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Place pecans in bottom.
Quarter biscuits and toss with sugar and cinnamon.
Place on top of pecans in pan. Mix melted margarine and brown sugar in saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Melt butter or margarine in deep skillet.
Add onion and pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in rice and tomato soups and water; heat to boiling: turn heat down and simmer.
Make 32 small meat balls with remaining ingredients.
Brown meat balls and drop into simmering sauce.
Cook slowly 45 to 60 minutes, or until sauce has thickened.
Serve at once.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in chicken, 1/4 cup picante, cream cheese and cumin.
Heat through.
Remove from heat. Stir in 1/2 cup of shredded cheese.
Heat oil in skillet, fry tortillas to soften, drain on paper towels.
Spoon chicken mixture into each tortilla; roll and place seam side down in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining picante and cheese over tortillas. Bake 15 minutes in 325° oven.
Top with onions.

title: peanut butter  balls
directions: Mix by hand margarine and 1/2 lb. powdered sugar. Add marshmallow creme, peanut butter and the rest of the sugar. Mixture will be thick.
Mix well and then refrigerate until very cold.
Roll into balls; place on a cookie sheet and freeze.

title: easy pecan rolls
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan with cinnamon.
Cover cinnamon with crushed pecans.
Slice one loaf of bread into 12 pieces and lay on top of the pecans.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook stew beef.
Leave small amount of water.
Cool.
Shred beef with fork until stringy.
Add mushroom soup.
Add enough water to water already in pot to equal 1 can.
Add sour cream.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook noodles. Pour Beef Stroganoff over noodles and serve.

title: lime fluff salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup heated pineapple juice.
You may need to add water to make 1/2 cup of liquid.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Add cream, marshmallows, cottage cheese and nuts.
Pour into mold.
Serves 8.

title: ranch stir-fry
directions: Heat vegetable oil in large skillet.
Add chicken strips. Stir in salad dressing packet.
Add vegetables and 2 tablespoons water.
Stir-fry about 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: In food processor, using the metal blade, chop the garlic. Add chunks of Blue cheese, cream cheese and butter and process. Add the shredded Cheddar cheese and process.
Form into two balls. Coat with the chopped nuts.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: a meal in a pan
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients.
After browning add in layers, sliced potatoes, sliced onions, sliced carrots, 2 teaspoons salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Steam in electric frypan with the vent closed until fork-tender, then if desired, leave vent open for last 10 minutes.
This serves 4 to 6 people and is very tasty; your whole meal is in one pan.

title: bacon omelet
directions: Bread eggs into a bowl and beat well.
Add milk and pinch of salt.
Melt margarine in skillet and add eggs.
Sprinkle pepper and bacon bits over eggs.
Fold and brown on both sides.

title: chicken salad
directions: Steam chicken in seasoned water; cool and shred.
Combine chicken with apples, celery, almonds and grapes.
Blend with mayonnaise and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: stuffed chicken shells
directions: Cook shells as directed on box; cool.
Mix cooked chicken, stuffing and Miracle Whip together.
Mix separately 3 cans of soup and 1/2 cup water.
Pour 1/3 of soup/water mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Stuff shells with chicken mixture and arrange shells over soup mixture in bottom of dish.
Pour remaining soup mixture over shells and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Warm soup, taco sauce, tomatoes and chopped chilies in saucepan.
Grate cheese.
Place tortillas in casserole dish.
Cover with meat mixture, then pour soup mixture over meat.
Top with cheese.
Cook in 400° oven for about 25 minutes or until heated well through.

title: simply delicious chocolate pie
directions: Mix filling at top speed 2 minutes. Pour into pie shell. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Turn off oven and allow to set an additional 10 minutes. Remove from oven. Cool and chill. Garnish with whipped cream, maraschino cherries or chocolate or peanut butter morsels.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: In top of double boiler beat egg whites, sugar, cream of tartar and water for one minute on high speed.
Place over boiling water (water should not touch bottom of pan).
Beat on high for 7 minutes.
Remove from boiling water.
Add vanilla and beat 2 more minutes.

title: curtis' chicken
directions: Whisk milk and eggs. Put cut up chicken in it. In separate bowl, mix toast and butter. Flour chicken, dip in milk, then again in the toast mixture. Put in greased baking pan.
