Bake at 400° for 35 minutes. Mix butter, onions, bell peppers, and garlic. Saute until tender. Pour over chicken when done then top with cheese.

title: cheese balls
directions: Place water, salt, nutmeg and butter in a 2-quart saucepan. Bring mixture to a full rolling boil over high heat.
Add flour all at once.
Remove pan from heat.
Stir until mixture forms a ball and leave sides of pan.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until mixture is smooth and shiny.
Add cheese and stir until blended.

title: bits 'o brickle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl mix Bits 'O Brickle with liquid shortening until evenly coated, then stir in 6 tablespoons flour until well coated.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Gradually add salt, baking soda and flour.
Mix well. Stir in coated Bits 'O Brickle.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 50 (2-inch) cookies).

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, pumpkin, cinnamon and Milnot and pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over this.
Melt oleo and drizzle over cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped pecans or walnuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Line pan with foil so you can turn it over to ice it.

title: basic dumplings
directions: Beat egg and milk until smooth.
Add (cooled) melted shortening.
Stir slightly to blend.
Pour into flour.
Mix only until soft dough forms.

title: red punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale. Chill. Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: very good cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order given.
Roll into balls. Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain fat.
Add next 4 ingredients. Grease an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Line pan with half of tortillas. Add half of meat mixture and half cheese.
Repeat tortillas, meat and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: candied apples
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil for 11 minutes.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Dip apples in candy and place on buttered sheet.
Insert popsicle sticks in center of apples for easier dipping.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and white vinegar well and add to other ingredients just before serving.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased baking pan at 400 degrees for 35 minutes or until brown on top.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a Ziploc bag, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Add biscuits and shake, coating all biscuits with sugar and cinnamon mixture. Place biscuits around greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter and pour cinnamon and sugar into butter.
Pour over top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turn out immediately.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and place in a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly and sprinkle over rhubarb mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.
Double everything for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: anise christmas meringues(40 meringues)
directions: Heat the oven to 250°.
Line baking sheets with foil.
With an electric mixer set at medium speed, beat the egg whites with the cream of tartar and salt until they hold soft peaks.
Increase speed to high and beat in the sugar gradually.
Continue beating until the whites hold stiff peaks.
Beat in the anise.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto the baking sheets. Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake until firm to the touch, 40 to 45 minutes.
Centers will still be soft.
Let stand about 30 seconds on baking sheets before removing.

title: dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and biscuits real fine.
Add sage, pepper, sugar and eggs.
While still warm, add butter.
Add chicken broth and onions.
Stir until smooth (at a medium consistency).
Salt to taste.
Bake until done.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Brown bacon; remove from grease.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in bacon grease.
Pour off grease.
Add soup, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, bay leaves and vinegar.
Season with salt and red pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add shrimp. Crumble bacon over top and serve over rice.

title: chicken and ham roll-ups
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 sheets of waxed paper; flatten with flat side of knife or mallet.
Top each piece of chicken with a slice of ham.
Roll up; secure with toothpicks.
In skillet, brown roll-ups in butter.
Mix soup and wine together; pour over chicken.
Cover; cook over low heat for 25 minutes, or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix. Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple in 9 x 12-inch dish, then cherry pie filling. Top with dry cake mix and chopped nuts.
Slice margarine in squares.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Cake will not look done until full 30 minutes is up.)

title: pasta salad
directions: Add any combination of onion, tomatoes, black olives, green pepper and cucumber.
Chop fine.

title: corn and broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and mix with corn, 1/4 cup cracker crumbs, egg, 1 tablespoon butter, onion, salt and pepper.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish (greased).
Place on topping: Mix 2 tablespoons butter, 1/4 cup cracker crumbs and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gillis tea bread
directions: Mix all together.
Spread into an 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until like a brownie.
Add cinnamon for variation if desired.

title: golden cheese sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar gradually, beating well.
Add flour, lemon juice, lemon rind, salt, sour cream, cottage cheese and butter; beat until almost smooth. Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in a slow oven (300°) for 1 hour or until set.
Serve cooled or well chilled, topped with fresh strawberries and whipped cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar together in a plastic bag.
Grease Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Open biscuits; cut into quarters.
Shake a few at a time in the plastic bag and place in the pan to make 1 layer.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Simmer for one hour on low.
Remove and discard spices before serving.
Serve hot. Serves 6 to 8.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Make crumbs of flour, brown sugar and oleo.
Put 1/2 cup of your crumb mixture
in a flat dish.
Reserve the rest for the topping.
Beat egg
whites,
sugar,
lemon
juice and strawberries together 10 minutes with
mixer.
Whip
cream
and fold into strawberry mixture.
Pour into dish; top with remaining crumbs and freeze.

title: michelle's strawberry delight cake
directions: Make cake mix (as on box); bake cake.
Mix together cut strawberries and glaze.
Put on cooled cake.
Add Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar for 20 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour and lemon extract.
Fold in 7-Up.
Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Use glaze on top or frost as desired.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add to macaroni and cheese. Add remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Melt one stick margarine and add to cookie crumbs.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Spoon ice cream over cookie layer. Sprinkle with peanuts, if desired.
Top with cooled topping.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain.
Set aside.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place triangles, with elongated points toward center, in a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press bottom and sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes on lower oven rack.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Spoon sausage over dough; sprinkle with cheeses.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients; pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° on lower oven rack for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8.

title: fried pie and dough
directions: Cream the sugar and lard together.
Add eggs and beat.
Add milk and beat.
Add remaining ingredients and work until it looks like pie dough.
Let stand for at least 2 hours in refrigerator or overnight.

title: apricot dessert
directions: Drain apricots and slice.
Dissolve jello in boiling water. Cool.
Reserve 1/2 cup jello and add apricots to remainder.
Pour into serving dish.
Fold Cool Whip into reserved jello and pour on top.
Chill.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crushed graham crackers and 1 stick oleo (melted).
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, 1 stick oleo and eggs for 10 minutes.
Spread on graham crackers.
Slice bananas.
Layer on.
Drain crushed pineapple.
Spread on top.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: bean dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Mix all ingredients until smooth. Cover with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in milk.
Mix water to eggs and beat.
Add to cooked rice and add sugar, vanilla and raisins.
Pour into dish and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Eat warm or cold.

title: debbie's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and garlic.
Add next 7 ingredients. Bring to a boil and simmer for one hour.
Mix Ricotta cheese with eggs, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon parsley leaves.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Pour into crust and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool and top with strawberries, which have been mashed and cooked with a little syrup, flour and a little lemon juice and margarine.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Cut ends off zucchini and grate.
Put in colander and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Squeeze water out of zucchini with hands.
When quite dry, saute in oil for 5 minutes. Cool.
Mix 2 cups zucchini with egg, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Press mixture into an 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cover with tomato sauce; sprinkle with oregano. Top with cheeses and arrange pepper strips over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: layered jello
directions: Layer each flavor of jello.
Layers 1, 3, 5 and 7 use 3/4 cup boiling water and 3/4 cup cold water.
Layers 2, 4 and 6 use 1/2 cup boiling water, 1/2 cup cold water and 1/2 cup evaporated milk. Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until almost set between each layer, then add the next.
Makes a very showy salad or light dessert.

title: mex-tex layered dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Set aside. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Set aside. Layer as follows:
bean dip, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture and sprinkle with onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Makes 24 servings.

title: broccoli-cheese dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine soup, broccoli, tomato, sour cream and mustard.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving. Serve with crackers and chips for dipping.

title: delicious cheesy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skin.
Cool, peel and chop coarsely.
Combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter over heat and melt.
Blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes and turn into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: vodka slush
directions: Mix boiling water and tea in large container and cool.
Add orange juice, lemonade and vodka and freeze.
Stir once.
This will not freeze solid.
Forms a slush.
Scoop into a glass.
Pour 7-Up or ginger ale pop over the top.

title: russian spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients together and store in an airtight container.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine in a saucepan.
Heat just until sugar dissolves and pour over vegetables.
Stir gently and marinate overnight before serving.

title: kung pao chicken
directions: Cook rice and
set
aside.
Chop all vegetables and set aside. Stir-fry diced chicken
in wok (wok must always be hot before adding oil)
in
olive
oil.
Stir-fry until tender and lightly browned.
Add
veggies
all
at
once to chicken.
Add peanuts or cashews and soy sauce as desired.
Serve over rice.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Line bottom of pan with vanilla wafers.
Mix together cream cheese, eggs, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour over vanilla wafers.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: congealed lime salad
directions: Mix Jell-0 and boiling water; stir well and fold in marshmallows.
Cut into 1/4's.
Mix in 1 small can of pineapple juice.
Set in refrigerator until it starts to thicken.
To the thickened mixture, add the other can of pineapple juice, cream cheese, mayonnaise, pecans and whipping cream.
After all is mixed, pour into a mold or a dish and set in refrigerator until firm.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine 1/2 cup syrup with gelatin.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Reserve 4/5 apricot halves for garnish.
Blend remaining apricots in blender until smooth.
Combine apricots and gelatin mixture.
In a large bowl beat cream cheese; then add milk and lemon juice.
Stir in the blended apricots.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Turn into graham cracker crusts and garnish with remaining apricots in two piece clusters.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Grease pie pan.
Mix ingredients well. Pour into pie pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.

title: teeny-weeny applesauce cupcakes
directions: Cream margarine until fluffy.
Beat eggs and sweetener until thick and lemon colored; add to margarine and mix well.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add to margarine mixture alternately with applesauce, starting and ending with dry.
Blend well after each addition.
Add vanilla; blend in raisins and nuts. Pour into tiny cupcake (tart) tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked bananas and pineapple
directions: Peel bananas.
Place in single layer in baking dish just large enough to hold.
Combine pineapple with juice, honey, lemon juice and cornstarch in a bowl.
Pour over bananas.
Dot with butter. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or just until bananas are soft.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Mix beef pieces, soup and drained mushrooms together in a crock-pot. Cook on low for 6 to 10 hours.
Stir in sour cream to taste before serving over cooked egg noodles.

title: indian fried bread
directions: Mix and let stand 20 minutes.
Divide into 5 or 6 portions and roll out on floured surface until about 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick. Fry in 1 inch of hot grease until brown, turning once.
Drain on paper sack.
Serve with beans or chili.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Dredge chicken with flour and pepper.
Brown each piece on all sides in hot oil.
Place skin side up in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish in single layer.
Spread undiluted soup evenly over each piece.
Sprinkle almonds.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until juice runs clear.
Yields 4 servings.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in large bowl; cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Best served with large or scoop Fritos.

title: jay's salsa
directions: Chop up tomatoes and jalapenos; add rest of ingredients.
Stir well.
Chill for 12 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dilly cheese ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In small bowl, combine margarine, cheese, dill weed and garlic powder. Separate each can of dough into 10 biscuits. Cut each biscuit in half and randomly place 20 pieces in an ungreased flute tube pan. Spoon 1/2 of cheese mixture over top. Repeat layers with remaining biscuit halves and cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 1 minute and remove from pan.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt
over
cucumbers,
onions,
green and red peppers and let stand 1 hour.
While this is standing, combine sugar, vinegar,
mustard and celery seeds and heat until sugar is melted.
Pack cucumbers in containers (plastic freezer) and pour juice over	and
freeze.
Easy
to	make and pickles stay crisp.

title: southwest dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender jar and blend at high for 2 to 3 minutes until well blended.
Or place in a medium size bowl and mix well by hand.
Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with tortilla chips or fresh veggies. Yield:
1 1/4 cups.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix 4 minutes.
Bake in Bundt pan at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes (until cake begins to pull away from pan).
Cool 15 minutes. Remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: iliana's "veal marsala"
directions: Saute veal in clear butter for 1 to 2 minutes.
Place veal on large platter (a nice platter for serving).
In same pan, saute mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Add beef bouillon and wine.
Cook down to a gravy.
(If you like, you can add a little cornstarch to thicken gravy to consistency you desire.)
Pour sauteed ingredients over veal and serve hot.

title: diabetics strawberry pie
directions: Boil water, Sugar Twin, cornstarch and salt until thick. Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Stir well.
Fill pie crust with fresh strawberries, then pour cooled filling over them.
Cover top with Cool Whip, if your diet allows it, or use sugar-free whipped topping.

title: banana split cake
directions: Step 1:
Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1 stick melted butter and 1 tablespoon sugar and spread in long pan.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour over cabbage.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: steak soup
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add other ingredients; season to taste.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat eggs, salt, milk, softened oleo and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead dough about 3 minutes on a floured board. Divide in 4 balls of dough.
Roll each ball very thin.
Cut in strips, then with flour in between, stack them.
Cut crosswise. Drop the cut pieces in boiling broth (either chicken or beef).

title: apple whipped sweet potatoes
directions: Place apples, sweet potatoes and apple juice in a 3-quart saucepan. Cover and cook over medium heat about 20 minutes or until tender. Drain. Add salt, spices, margarine and sugar to mixture. Mash with mixer or by hand until potatoes are smooth. (I liked this better when I put mixture in blender and blended until smooth. You could also use a food processor.) Spread mixture in ovenproof serving dish. Sprinkle with nuts. (You can also cover with miniature marshmallows.) Bake at 350° about 15 minutes or until marshmallows are melted and lightly browned. Serve hot. Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt edna's cushaw pie
directions: Add drained and mashed cushaw, sugar, flour, margarine, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shells.
Top with favorite spice.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.
Will make 2 large pies.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles following directions on package; drain.
Return to pan; add cauliflower and broccoli, soup, sour cream, onion, salt, pepper, chicken and cheese.
Mix gently.
Transfer to a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: sweet and sour ribs
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and pepper on wax paper or plastic bag.
Roll ribs in mixture, coating them on all sides.
Shake off excess.

title: crock-pot fajitas
directions: See Dan Wathor for secret recipe!

title: hot enchilada squares
directions: Crumble ground beef and onion in frying pan; brown and drain. Pour meat mixture in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. In bowl, combine eggs, tomato sauce, milk, chili powder, Tabasco sauce, cumin and oregano. Pour over meat; sprinkle with olives, chilies and chips. Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and cook another 5 minutes.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix honey, peanut butter and vanilla in a small bowl until creamy.
Mix milk in 2 tablespoons at a time.
Knead dough for 2 or 3 minutes.
If dough is sticky, add extra milk.
If dough is dry, add a few drops of water.
Form dough into desired shapes.
Store in airtight container.
Play dough will keep for a few days.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan and layer macaroni, meat mixture, cheese and mushrooms.
Cover with pepperoni.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn mague choux
directions: In large skillet, combine butter and oil with corn, onion, sugar, pepper, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Cook over high heat until corn is tender and starch starts to form a crust on the pan bottom, about 12 to 14 minutes, stirring occasionally, and stirring more as mixture starts sticking.
Gradually stir in 1 cup of the stock, scraping the pan bottom to remove crust as you stir.
Continue cooking 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the margarine, stir until melted and cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently and scraping pan bottom as needed.
Reduce heat to low and cook about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, then about 15 minutes, stirring fairly frequently.
Add the remaining 1 cup stock and cook about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in 1/2 cup milk and continue cooking until most of the liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: Season potatoes with salt and pepper; add 1 chopped egg white; mix
and set aside.
Combine vinegar, water and mustard in small jar and shake.
In mixing bowl, mash two boiled eggs; add raw egg yolk; mix with fork or mixer.
Add oil, gradually; mixture with get very thick.
Add ingredients from jar;	blend until smooth. Pour dressing on potatoes.	Serves 6.

title: pizzelles(the best)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop onto pizzelle iron and cook until golden.

title: chimichangas
directions: Cook roast in crock-pot or oven until tender.
Shred roast and place back in crock-pot, adding green chilies, onion, salsa, salt and pepper.
Continue to cook so all the flavors combine.
Warm tortillas one at a time in microwave 20 seconds.
Using slotted spoon, drain roast mixture (1 spoonful at a time).
Place in center of warmed tortillas.
Add cheese, then fold in both ends and roll. Secure with a toothpick.
Place in hot oil, enough to just turn and brown on both sides.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry. Set aside.
Heat oil and garlic in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and brown. Remove chicken and set aside.
Add onion and green pepper to skillet. Saute until tender.
Pour off fat.
Return chicken to skillet. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer over low heat 30 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove bay leaf before serving.
You may serve over rice or noodles.

title: biscuits
directions: Use a large mixing bowl and fill 3/4 full with flour.
Mix flour and baking soda.
Add buttermilk and mix until the dough is stiff, but still soft enough to work with. Turn on a floured board.
Turn 2 or 3 times until coated with flour.
Pinch off dough about the size of a tennis ball or if you want larger biscuits, the size of a baseball.
Place on a greased baking sheet and flatten out with a tablespoon that has been dipped in bacon fat. Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes. Turn temperature to broil and brown the top.
Makes 24 to 30 biscuits.

title: pineapple poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool cake 15 minutes.
Poke holes in cake at 1/2-inch intervals.
While cake is cooking, cook pineapple and sugar; spread over cake.
Prepare pudding as directed and spread over pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle pecans on top.

title: fudgsicles
directions: To chocolate pudding, add the 1/2 cup sugar and cream and milk as called for on box.
Mix and pour into ice tubs and freeze.

title: tomato-herb bread
directions: Measure the tomato juice and pour into large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over juice and stir to dissolve.
Add honey.
Beat in one egg.
Add the first 4 cups of flour, one cup at a time, stirring briskly after each addition.
After adding flour, beat the mixture 100 strokes, until very smooth.
Cover bowl and let dough rest 45 minutes in warm place.

title: pecan pie
directions: In mixing bowl, break eggs and beat slightly with fork.
Add salt, Karo syrup and sugar.
Stir in egg with fork.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Can use halves or chopped (halves make a prettier pie).
Pour in prepared pie shell (uncooked).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or whenever pecans are golden in color.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour and soda together.
Blend dry ingredients with cream mixture.
Add potato chips and nuts.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet; press lightly with fork.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken saute
directions: Saute the peppers, tomatoes, zucchini and onions in the olive oil (the amount of ingredients depends on the number of servings needed).
Add chicken, garlic, basil and oregano.
Simmer until done.
Serve over rice.

title: spinach dip
directions: The night before, mix sour cream, mayonnaise and dry soup mix. Refrigerate overnight.

title: oatmeal candy cookies
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a full boil. Boil for 3 minutes and add the oatmeal, pecans and vanilla. Beat until mixture begins to thicken. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: french-style chicken
directions: Melt margarine in a large pot.
Add flour to make a paste. Add water to make a sauce.
Mix spices with sauce.
Put chicken and vegetables in sauce and stir.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add the tomato sauce, soup and seasoning packet and heat to boiling.
Put in layers with tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese on top of each layer.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted.

title: meat loaf with gravy
directions: Mix hamburger, salt and pepper.
Shape into a loaf.
Tear a long piece of foil and place on cookie sheet or a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place the meat in middle of foil.
Mix the two soups together and pour over the meat.
Sprinkle the dry soup mix on top.
Bring foil over the top and seal all edges.
Put in a preheated 350° oven and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: blushing mushrooms
directions: Drain mushrooms, melt butter in skillet.
Add mushrooms, saute until browned, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice. Combine chives, flour, paprika, salt and pepper; sprinkle over mushrooms.
Mix sour cream until smooth.
Pour sour cream over mushrooms.
Serve hot with toothpick.

title: green chili stewroswell, new mexico
directions: Brown stew meat and onions in a large stew pot, 8 qts. at least.
Add salt, pepper, rosemary, oregano, thyme, etc.
Use the leaf type, it makes people wonder what the sam hill it is!
Add water to about half the pot, cover and cook until the meat is tender.
An hour or so, depending on how tough and cheap the meat is.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove chicken from pot and debone. Cook spaghetti and onion in chicken broth (season to taste).
To spaghetti add green chilies and soups.
Stir well.
Pour into baking dish with chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted and mixture is hot and bubbly.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water, shortening and salt to a boil.
Stir in flour and cook until dough forms a smooth ball and leaves sides of saucepan clean.
Then remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake 25 minutes more.
Cool.
Slit and fill with sweetened whipped cream or pudding filling.
Yield:
12 large cream puffs.

title: baked fudge
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour, cocoa and salt until well blended. Mix in margarine.
Add pecans and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Set pan in a 10 x 13-inch roasting pan.
Pour boiling water into roasting pan to measure 1-inch.
Bake 45 minutes at 325° or until it is set and crusty on top.
Do not overbake.
Remove from oven to wire rack. Cool.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.
Serve with whipped topping.
Can be served warm.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.
Very rich.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Dip the chicken breasts in mixture.
Melt butter on baking dish large enough to hold the chicken.
Place chicken in butter with meaty side down. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 375°.
In saucepan, mix soup and mushrooms and heat.
Remove from heat.
Add wine.
Flip the chicken breasts over.
Pour on the sauce.
Bake 20 minutes longer, uncovered.
Serve chicken with sauce.

title: mushroom loaf
directions: Saute onions until soft in margarine.
Add mushrooms; brown slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: sweet potato sausage cakes
directions: Shred raw sweet potatoes and mix with sausage and salt.
Shape into 10 flat cakes.
Place in cold skillet and place over low heat.
Fry slowly until brown and crisp on both sides.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: caramel pound cake
directions: Beat all ingredients with electric mixer for about 5 minutes. Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake for about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Add celery, onion and pepper.
Cook 3 minutes. Add cooked rice and soup.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Pour into dish. Top with olives and nuts.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: girl scout brownie's favorite camp brownie
directions: Cream together butter, oil and sugar.
Blend in eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients (except chips and nuts) and zucchini.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: old-fashioned peanut patties
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add next 3 ingredients.
Beat with mixer or by hand until creamy.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Be sure it is beaten until creamy.
Yields 10 to 12 patties.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour crushed pineapple with juice into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour cherry pie filling over pineapple. Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit mixture.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix. Sprinkle nuts over top of cake mix. Do not stir. Bake for 55 minutes.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Spread bean dip in bottom of a large shallow pan, then avocado.
Sprinkle and mix together garlic salt, lemon juice and avocado.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning; set aside before spreading over avocados.
Then layer tomatoes and olives, then layer cheese dip and jalapenos.
Spread green onions on top.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and lemon extract.
Gradually stir in the sweetened condensed milk.
Add egg yolks; stir until blended. Pour into crust.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely, then put whipped cream on top.
Store in refrigerator.
Freezes well for a later date.

title: pecan cheese wafers
directions: Combine cheese and butter; mixing well.
Combine flour, salt, and pepper and add to creamed mixture; mixing well.
Stir in cereal.
Chill dough for 2 hours.

title: blizzard(a blender drink with kahlua)
directions: Add all ingredients to a blender with ice and blend until nice and frothy.
Be careful; the alcohol sneaks up on you!

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and brown lightly.
Add spaghetti sauce (I use one extra spicy) and 1 1/2 cups water. Then add rice.
Cover and simmer.
You may need more rice.
Season to taste.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Mix Cool Whip, egg and cake mix together.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesecake
directions: In a medium bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Measure applesauce into crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover; cook on high for a few hours.
Remove cover during last half of cooking.
Stir occasionally.
Pour into clear jars and seal with flats and rings.

title: hot christmas punch
directions: Put brown sugar, candy, cinnamon sticks and cloves in coffee pot basket.
Pour cranberry juice, pineapple juice and water into coffee pot.
Percolate the mixture.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's chicken
directions: Combine chicken soup
and sour cream.
Combine stuffing and chicken broth.
Layer
9 x 13-inch greased baking pan with chicken and vegetables.
Top
with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes to an hour.

title: clam whiffle
directions: Combine milk and crackers in bowl; soak for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole and bake for 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven until puffy and golden.

title: mommie dot's famous roast beef pie
directions: Mix pie ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into pie pan.
Cover with pie shell which is just soft enough to lay flat.
Puncture shell several times with fork and pat with butter (or squeeze margarine).
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 400°.

title: moravian orange cake(makes 2 cakes)
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Add softened margarine.
Gradually add tap water to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add potatoes, eggs and 1/2 cup of flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm, draft-free place until double in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: chef's delight
directions: Check wallet for money; dash to bank as needed.
Stop at take out restaurant and place order.
Transfer money to cashier.
Bring food home and serve to hungry family.

title: easy cherry dessert
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put cherry filling evenly in pan.
Cover with
dry
cake mix.
Slice 1/2 pound butter or oleo over top of
cake
mix
and
bake until bubbly and brown. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
May use any type of pie filling.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add onion and clams; saute over low heat for 5 minutes.
In large Pyrex bowl, combine soups and half and half; stir thoroughly.
Pour margarine and clam mixture into soup.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours; stir each hour.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix milk with beaten egg.
Add dry ingredients to the milk and egg mixture.
Do not overmix. Cook in hot oil.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions and cool completely. Cut in 1/2 lengthwise.
Cook flour and milk; stir frequently until thick.
Cool completely.
Beat sugar, oleo or margarine and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour/milk mixture.
Beat 10 minutes. Put flour, milk, sugar, oleo mixture on bottom 1/2 of cake.
Top with other 1/2 cake.
Frost all sides with your favorite chocolate icing. If your filling is a little runny, place in refrigerator a few minutes before adding top layer.

title: bittersweet chocolate icing
directions: Boil just 3 minutes.
Beat until stiff enough to spread, not too long.

title: cottontail club(daddy's stuff)
directions: Sear all meat in olive oil.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic salt, sage and Italian seasoning.
Remove meat from pan and saute onions, then put meat back in pan.
Add tomato sauce, diced peppers and juice.
Add water to cover meat.
Simmer 1/2 hour and add wine.
Simmer another 1 1/2 hours.
Thicken with flour.
Add a dash of soda just before serving (blend fat into gravy).
Serve over mashed potatoes, rice or polenta.
Seasonings may be adjusted to taste.

title: shish kebab
directions: Cut meat in 1 x 1-inch cubes.
Mix salad dressing according to directions on package, pour over meat that has been placed in a shallow casserole dish.
Marinate in the refrigerator at least 10 hours.
Cut up the peppers, onions and mushrooms.
When placing ingredients on the stick always have a pepper and onion next to the meat.
We start with a pepper, add meat, then onions, tomato, mushroom, pepper, meat, onion and so on.
Grill 4 minutes on 1 side, turn a 1/4 turn and cook for 4 minutes, continue until the whole shish kebab is cooked.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix together the first 5 items and then add apples.
Pour 1/2 batter into well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle half of the cinnamon mixture on top.
Pour rest of batter over cinnamon and top with rest of cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pistou(soup)
directions: Saute the onions and leek in butter.
Transfer to a large pot with cover.
Add green beans, potatoes, tomatoes and beef bouillon. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and spaghetti; cook 15 minutes.
In a bowl mash garlic with basil, thyme and sage.
Add egg yolks and gradually stir in the oil and tomato paste.
Add a little soup to this and stir back into soup.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: blueberry cream cheese squares
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, water and blueberries in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Cool.

title: foolproof crust
directions: Cut flour and salt into butter; mix until a ball forms.
Put dough with hands into a 9-inch pie plate, mending if necessary and fluting edge, if desired.
Prick generously with a fork and bake at 400° for 7 minutes.

title: linguini pasta salad
directions: Boil linguini until tender but firm, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Combine linguini with the other ingredients and toss until the linguini is well coated. Refrigerate.

title: butterscotch chip cookies
directions: Mix in order given and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy pecan pralines
directions: Mix sugar and evaporated milk well and let come to a boil. Add pecans and cook until mixture forms a soft ball when a bit is dropped into cold water.
Add salt.
Remove from heat and beat slightly until mixture begins to hold shape.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: armadillo eggs-hall
directions: Mix cheese, sausage and biscuit mix.
Knead until thoroughly mixed.
Slit peppers and rinse to remove seeds.
Stuff each pepper with cheese and pinch closed around cheese.
Pinch a bit of sausage-cheese mixture
and flatten to 1/4-inch pancake.
Place cheese stuffed pepper in middle of dough and wrap completely, sealing the ends.
Roll back and forth to mold into egg shape. Roll each "egg" in Shake 'N Bake; dip in beaten eggs, then in Shake 'N Bake again.
Bake in slow oven, 300° to 325°, for 20 to 25 minutes.
Best served slightly warm.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Put on a cookie sheet, then put on shredded Cheddar cheese, lettuce (chopped), sliced olives, diced green peppers and diced tomatoes.

title: aunt julia's tarellis cookies
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: mocha
directions: Add coffee slowly to syrup in double boiler. Blend well.
Add milk, salt and vanilla. Heat to serve as you would hot chocolate.

title: janie poole's pancakes
directions: Mix all together.
Pour by 1/4 cupfuls onto hot griddle. Makes twelve 4-inch pancakes.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients all together on high for 15 minutes. Blend in a small container of Cool Whip.
Put in a baked pie shell and bake.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: cube steak
directions: Season and flour steak.
Brown in 2 tablespoons of Crisco. Add pepper, onion and tomatoes.
Simmer about 45 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup water to make gravy.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: tuna apple salad
directions: In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Add apples, onion, celery and tuna.
Toss until well mixed.
Chill 4 hours or more before serving.
Serve on bed of lettuce.
Divide evenly. Makes 2 servings.
Each serving provides: 1/2 milk exchange, 1 fat exchange, 1 fruit exchange, 5 vegetable exchanges and 2 protein exchanges.

title: jello cranberry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream well. Add nuts and spread on top.

title: gooey butter cookies
directions: Mix with mixer until well blended. Chill dough. Roll into balls. Roll in powdered sugar. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tomatoes picante
directions: Put tomatoes in deep bowl. In jar, combine remaining ingredients.
Shake well.
Pour over tomatoes.
Chill 3 hours or overnight. Spoon marinade over tomatoes occasionally.
To serve, drain tomatoes and place on lettuce and garnish.
Serves 6.

title: holiday turkey
directions: Wipe turkey with damp towel.
Rub inside with lemon, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Loosely stuff body and neck cavities with dressing allowing 1 cup per pound of meat.
Truss bird by tying legs, running string under wings, back to legs and tie.
Rub butter or oil over entire outside of turkey.
Roast in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes; turn on other side and roast for 45 minutes more. Turn on back and roast for 2 hours, basting with butter or oil every 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumber casserole
directions: Combine cucumbers and water in a saucepan, bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until tender. Drain well. Cook bacon until crisp, drain, reserving 3 tbsp. drippings. Crumble bacon, set aside.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender; drain.
Saute onion in butter and combine with carrots.
Heat soup, 1/2 teaspoon salt, dash of pepper and 1/2 cup diced cheese, until melted.
Pour over cooked carrots.
Pour all into greased 8 x 8-inch pan and top with croutons tossed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until topping is browned.

title: easy egg drop soup
directions: Mix cornstarch, water and oil.
Boil 3 cups of chicken broth and add the cornstarch mixture.
Rapidly stir in 1 beaten egg stirring until strands are cooked.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Mix and pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish. Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: french's italian chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
In skillet, heat oil and brown chicken.
Stir in spaghetti seasoning, water and tomato paste.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes or until thickened.
Sprinkle on cheese and let it melt.

title: lime salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine vegetables; stir in dressing. Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: strawberry pineapple cake
directions: In a large pitcher or punch bowl, stir together juices and add water.
Stir gently.
Add ice ring and strawberries.
Makes approximately 15 (4 oz.) servings.

title: escalloped eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into cubes.
Cook in water until tender (5 to 10 minutes).
Drain eggplant thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper, then mash.
Mash tomatoes; mix with onion, eggplant, eggs and cornbread.
May add chopped green pepper, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a large casserole dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for the first 1/2 hour.
Remove lid for the last 15 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and oil potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut in half and spoon out potatoes.
With electric mixer, add canned milk, Velveeta cheese and diced stuffed olives.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Fill shells and sprinkle with paprika and grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Make and refrigerate a few hours before baking or day before.

title: broccoli and cheddar soup
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add onion and cook until golden, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour, salt, thyme, nutmeg and pepper; cook 2 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: cherry cream cakes
directions: Line muffin tins with paper cups.
Put vanilla cookie in bottom of each cup.
Have cream cheese at room temperature. Cream the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Mix until light and fluffy.
Fill cups 2/3 full of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
When cool, spoon 2 teaspoons cherry pie filling on top of each.
Makes 22 to 24 cakes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in glass jar, putting 3 or 4 pieces of garlic in each jar.
Use 1 teaspoon of dill seed to 1 quart of pickles. If using pint jars, use only 1/2 teaspoon of dill seed per pint. Boil water, vinegar and salt, making sure that the ingredients are dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix dry jello and cake mix.
Add oil and water.
Mix well. Add strawberry juice and mix well.
Add eggs.
Bake in layers 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: cherry ice cream *
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add condensed milk and vanilla; blend well.
Cut cherries into small pieces.
Stir in cherries, juice and half of homogenized milk. Pour into freezer container; add remaining milk until almost full. Makes 1 gallon.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in two graham cracker crusts.
Makes 2 pies.
